{"type":"text","timestamp":1778636730195,"sessionID":"ses_1e0fdff35ffeMtwtH2o5c8Lf8v","part":{"id":"prt_e1f02acf9001Biib0pfIdcS2uC","messageID":"msg_e1f023fb90010QuDZayz5qIV9Z","sessionID":"ses_1e0fdff35ffeMtwtH2o5c8Lf8v","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a micro-opt hypothesis to eliminate false load-use stalls by making the hazard detector source-use aware. This targets CoreMark cycles directly with minimal RTL risk and no contract changes.","time":{"start":1778636729593,"end":1778636730194},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_02812eb27f141c90016a03d7b9723c8199a4962bc2d625f41f","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778636735010,"sessionID":"ses_1e0fdff35ffeMtwtH2o5c8Lf8v","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_KNcSNAsrAApUQarLUFp7m1bV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r1s0\n+title: Source-aware load-use stalls\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use interlock compares a load destination against both\n+  instruction bitfields that look like rs1 and rs2, even when the following\n+  instruction does not architecturally read one or both sources. CoreMark has\n+  dense load and immediate/control sequences, so false one-cycle bubbles can\n+  reduce iterations per cycle without improving correctness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Make the hazard unit source-use aware for the IF/ID instruction. Keep the\n+  existing true load-use interlock, but only compare rs1 for instructions that\n+  actually read rs1 and only compare rs2 for instructions that actually read\n+  rs2. This should remove spurious stalls after loads for OP-IMM, LOAD, JALR,\n+  LUI, AUIPC, JAL, FENCE, and SYSTEM encodings while preserving all real RAW\n+  hazards and the existing RVFI retirement behavior.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Derive IF/ID rs1/rs2-use predicates from the opcode/funct class and gate the load-use dependency comparisons with those predicates.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the full IF/ID instruction, or equivalent source-use signals, into the hazard unit instead of relying on unconditional rs1/rs2 bitfield comparisons.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,24 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r1s0\n+title: Source-aware load-use stalls\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use interlock compares a load destination against both\n+  instruction bitfields that look like rs1 and rs2, even when the following\n+  instruction does not architecturally read one or both sources. CoreMark has\n+  dense load and immediate/control sequences, so false one-cycle bubbles can\n+  reduce iterations per cycle without improving correctness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Make the hazard unit source-use aware for the IF/ID instruction. Keep the\n+  existing true load-use interlock, but only compare rs1 for instructions that\n+  actually read rs1 and only compare rs2 for instructions that actually read\n+  rs2. This should remove spurious stalls after loads for OP-IMM, LOAD, JALR,\n+  LUI, AUIPC, JAL, FENCE, and SYSTEM encodings while preserving all real RAW\n+  hazards and the existing RVFI retirement behavior.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Derive IF/ID rs1/rs2-use predicates from the opcode/funct class and gate the load-use dependency comparisons with those predicates.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the full IF/ID instruction, or equivalent source-use signals, into the hazard unit instead of relying on unconditional rs1/rs2 bitfield comparisons.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,24 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r1s0\n+title: Source-aware load-use stalls\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use interlock compares a load destination against both\n+  instruction bitfields that look like rs1 and rs2, even when the following\n+  instruction does not architecturally read one or both sources. CoreMark has\n+  dense load and immediate/control sequences, so false one-cycle bubbles can\n+  reduce iterations per cycle without improving correctness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Make the hazard unit source-use aware for the IF/ID instruction. Keep the\n+  existing true load-use interlock, but only compare rs1 for instructions that\n+  actually read rs1 and only compare rs2 for instructions that actually read\n+  rs2. This should remove spurious stalls after loads for OP-IMM, LOAD, JALR,\n+  LUI, AUIPC, JAL, FENCE, and SYSTEM encodings while preserving all real RAW\n+  hazards and the existing RVFI retirement behavior.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Derive IF/ID rs1/rs2-use predicates from the opcode/funct class and gate the load-use dependency comparisons with those predicates.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the full IF/ID instruction, or equivalent source-use signals, into the hazard unit instead of relying on