 and frequent backward branches, making a very small front-end predictor likely to improve iterations per cycle without the LUT and Fmax cost of a larger dynamic predictor.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add a static predict-taken path in IF for aligned backward conditional branches and aligned unconditional JAL, while keeping forward conditional branches predicted not-taken and JALR resolved in EX. Carry the predicted next PC through ID/EX, compare it against the actual EX-resolved next PC, and redirect only on mispredict. This should remove most loop-back branch penalties with only immediate decode/add logic in the fetch path and no predictor RAM state.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 6, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to the IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles so EX can validate the IF-stage prediction while preserving RVFI pc_wdata semantics.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Decode fetched branch/JAL immediates in IF and choose aligned pc+imm for backward conditional branches and JAL, otherwise pc+4; emit the chosen predicted next PC with the fetched instruction.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Latch the IF-stage predicted next PC into ID/EX alongside the existing decoded instruction metadata.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage....","metadata":{"matches":4,"truncated":false},"title":"critical path|fmax|MUL|multipl|alu|Tang|lut|micro_opt|source-aware|load-use","time":{"start":1778639813597,"end":1778639813632}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_040d61f60343c8c4016a03e3c55fe8819985ddd383de9c5267"}},"id":"prt_e1f31bba300176pkajWK2bgY9H","sessionID":"ses_1e0ce96a4ffeI725GK5eP7uNWf","messageID":"msg_e1f31966a001lN2xEe1rifgbn2"}}
