{"type":"text","timestamp":1778636738491,"sessionID":"ses_1e0fdffa1fferQ02u5XDIVUhUP","part":{"id":"prt_e1f02cf69001L1WO16RWi0yl61","messageID":"msg_e1f0254d8002d74C7DpzUq2Zmd","sessionID":"ses_1e0fdffa1fferQ02u5XDIVUhUP","type":"text","text":"The strongest structural angle is to remove rare DIV/REM operations from the single-cycle EX ALU path. A small iterative divide/remainder unit should lift FPGA Fmax and LUT pressure while only stalling on DIV/REM, which CoreMark uses little or not at all compared with MUL.","time":{"start":1778636738409,"end":1778636738489},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0518d677536cba8d016a03d7c228948198af813da9b10534e5","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778636748735,"sessionID":"ses_1e0fdffa1fferQ02u5XDIVUhUP","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_THWMuZivSpba3FC38REU1wWy","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r1s1\n+title: \"Move DIV/REM off the ALU critical path\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current execute stage contains a fully combinational RV32IM ALU, including\n+  SystemVerilog division and remainder operators in the same result mux as the\n+  common RV32I and MUL operations. On the Tang Nano 20K this likely bloats LUT\n+  usage and lengthens the EX critical path even though CoreMark is dominated by\n+  ordinary integer, load/store, branch, and multiply instructions rather than\n+  divide/remainder.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU out of the combinational ALU into a small iterative\n+  multi-cycle M-extension side unit in EX. Keep ADD/SUB/logic/shift/compare and\n+  the MUL-family operations on the existing single-cycle path, but detect divide\n+  and remainder opcodes in EX, start the divider, and stall the pipeline until\n+  the result is available. This structural decoupling should reduce the normal\n+  ALU critical path and LUT pressure with negligible CoreMark CPI cost because\n+  rare DIV/REM instructions pay the added latency only when they occur.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real DIV/REM operators from the combinational ALU path while preserving ALTOPS behavior for formal builds.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add DIV/REM detection, launch/consume the iterative result, and hold the EX/MEM register while a divide operation is in progress.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an execute-stage multi-cycle stall input so IF/ID and ID/EX hold correctly while the divider is busy.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the new execute-stage divider stall into the global hazard and pipeline hold controls without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/div_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a compact iterative RV32 divider/remainder unit that implements divide-by-zero and INT_MIN/-1 semantics exactly.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Update or extend M-extension tests so DIV/REM correctness is checked through the new multi-cycle path as well as the remaining ALU operations.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r1s1\n+title: \"Move DIV/REM off the ALU critical path\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current execute stage contains a fully combinational RV32IM ALU, including\n+  SystemVerilog division and remainder operators in the same result mux as the\n+  common RV32I and MUL operations. On the Tang Nano 20K this likely bloats LUT\n+  usage and lengthens the EX critical path even though CoreMark is dominated by\n+  ordinary integer, load/store, branch, and multiply instructions rather than\n+  divide/remainder.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU out of the combinational ALU into a small iterative\n+  multi-cycle M-extension side unit in EX. Keep ADD/SUB/logic/shift/compare and\n+  the MUL-family operations on the existing single-cycle path, but detect divide\n+  and remainder opcodes in EX, start the divider, and stall the pipeline until\n+  the result is available. This structural decoupling should reduce the normal\n+  ALU critical path and LUT pressure with negligible CoreMark CPI cost because\n+  rare DIV/REM instructions pay the added latency only when they occur.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real DIV/REM operators from the combinational ALU path while preserving ALTOPS behavior for formal builds.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add DIV/REM detection, launch/consume the iterative result, and hold the EX/MEM register while a divide operation is in progress.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an execute-stage multi-cycle stall input so IF/ID and ID/EX hold correctly while the divider is busy.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the new execute-stage divider stall into the global hazard and pipeline hold controls without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/div_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a compact iterative RV32 divider/remainder unit that implements divide-by-zero and INT_MIN/-1 semantics exactly.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Update or extend M-extension tests so DIV/REM correctness is checked through the new multi-cycle path as well as the remaining ALU operations.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n==================================================================