{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778636733329,"sessionID":"ses_1e0fe0014ffekWyq2QBqxsnnLZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_O7I7vkLzvxpCUxVZ0yeTtUd5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r1s2\n+title: \"Static backward branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core resolves all branches and jumps in EX, so every taken loop branch or JAL pays a two-instruction flush penalty. CoreMark has tight loops and frequent backward branches, making a very small front-end predictor likely to improve iterations per cycle without the LUT and Fmax cost of a larger dynamic predictor.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a static predict-taken path in IF for backward conditional branches and unconditional JAL, while keeping forward conditional branches predicted not-taken and JALR resolved in EX. Carry the predicted next PC through ID/EX, compare it against the actual EX-resolved next PC, and redirect only on mispredict. This should remove most loop-back branch penalties with only immediate decode/add logic in the fetch path and no predictor RAM state.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to the IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles so EX can validate the IF-stage prediction while preserving RVFI pc_wdata semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Decode fetched branch/JAL immediates in IF and choose pc+imm for backward conditional branches and JAL, otherwise pc+4; emit the chosen predicted next PC with the fetched instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch the IF-stage predicted next PC into ID/EX alongside the existing decoded instruction metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare actual next PC from branch/jump resolution against the predicted next PC and assert redirect only when they differ, including taken-forward, not-taken-backward, JALR, and misalignment-trap cases.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r1s2\n+title: \"Static backward branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core resolves all branches and jumps in EX, so every taken loop branch or JAL pays a two-instruction flush penalty. CoreMark has tight loops and frequent backward branches, making a very small front-end predictor likely to improve iterations per cycle without the LUT and Fmax cost of a larger dynamic predictor.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a static predict-taken path in IF for backward conditional branches and unconditional JAL, while keeping forward conditional branches predicted not-taken and JALR resolved in EX. Carry the predicted next PC through ID/EX, compare it against the actual EX-resolved next PC, and redirect only on mispredict. This should remove most loop-back branch penalties with only immediate decode/add logic in the fetch path and no predictor RAM state.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to the IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles so EX can validate the IF-stage prediction while preserving RVFI pc_wdata semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Decode fetched branch/JAL immediates in IF and choose pc+imm for backward conditional branches and JAL, otherwise pc+4; emit the chosen predicted next PC with the fetched instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch the IF-stage predicted next PC into ID/EX alongside the existing decoded instruction metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare actual next PC from branch/jump resolution against the predicted next PC and assert redirect only when they differ, including taken-forward, not-taken-backward, JALR, and misalignment-trap cases.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r1s2\n+title: \"Static backward branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core resolves all branches and jumps in EX, so every taken loop branch or JAL pays a two-instruction flush penalty. CoreMark has tight loops and frequent backward branches, making a very small front-end predictor likely to improve iterations per cycle without the LUT and Fmax cost of a