{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778636754403,"sessionID":"ses_1e0fe0014ffekWyq2QBqxsnnLZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_s9pNDAMoPPThbOqy0Iw2CFbP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260512-003-r1s2\n2: title: \"Static backward branch predictor\"\n3: category: predictor\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The current five-stage core resolves all branches and jumps in EX, so every taken loop branch or JAL pays a two-instruction flush penalty. CoreMark has tight loops and frequent backward branches, making a very small front-end predictor likely to improve iterations per cycle without the LUT and Fmax cost of a larger dynamic predictor.\n6: hypothesis: |\n7:   Add a static predict-taken path in IF for aligned backward conditional branches and aligned unconditional JAL, while keeping forward conditional branches predicted not-taken and JALR resolved in EX. Carry the predicted next PC through ID/EX, compare it against the actual EX-resolved next PC, and redirect only on mispredict. This should remove most loop-back branch penalties with only immediate decode/add logic in the fetch path and no predictor RAM state.\n8: expected_impact:\n9:   fitness_delta_pct: 6\n10:   confidence: medium\n11: changes:\n12:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n13:     description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to the IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles so EX can validate the IF-stage prediction while preserving RVFI pc_wdata semantics.\"\n14:   - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n15:     description: \"Decode fetched branch/JAL immediates in IF and choose aligned pc+imm for backward conditional branches and JAL, otherwise pc+4; emit the chosen predicted next PC with the fetched instruction.\"\n16:   - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n17:     description: \"Latch the IF-stage predicted next PC into ID/EX alongside the existing decoded instruction metadata.\"\n18:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n19:     description: \"Compare actual next PC from branch/jump resolution against the predicted next PC and assert redirect only when they differ, including taken-forward, not-taken-backward, JALR, and misalignment-trap cases.\"\n\n(End of file - total 19 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-003-r1s2\ntitle: \"Static backward branch predictor\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The current five-stage core resolves all branches and jumps in EX, so every taken loop branch or JAL pays a two-instruction flush penalty. CoreMark has tight loops and frequent backward branches, making a very small front-end predictor likely to improve iterations per cycle without the LUT and Fmax cost of a larger dynamic predictor.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a static predict-taken path in IF for aligned backward conditional branches and aligned unconditional JAL, while keeping forward conditional branches predicted not-taken and JALR resolved in EX. Carry the predicted next PC through ID/EX, compare it against the actual EX-resolved next PC, and redirect only on mispredict. This should remove most loop-back branch penalties with only immediate decode/add logic in the fetch path and no predictor RAM state.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to the IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles so EX can validate the IF-stage prediction while preserving RVFI pc_wdata semantics.\"\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Decode fetched branch/JAL immediates in IF and choose aligned pc+imm for backward conditional branches and JAL, otherwise pc+4; emit the chosen predicted next PC with the fetched instruction.\"\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: \"Latch the IF-stage predicted next PC into ID/EX alongside the existing decoded instruction metadata.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Compare actual next PC from branch/jump resolution against the predicted next PC and assert redirect only when they differ, including taken-forward, not-taken-backward, JALR, and misalignment-trap cases.\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778636754395,"end":1778636754402}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b1521796129346b016a03d7d17eb4819a9e486556a1b1a16f"}},"id":"prt_e1f030ab8001ErGVMP3qmw1RIv","sessionID":"ses_1e0fe0014ffekWyq2QBqxsnnLZ","messageID":"msg_e1f0300360016M6c6zdaf6zO2J"}}
