{"type":"text","timestamp":1778639842266,"sessionID":"ses_1e0ce95d2ffeVyPB3QV5a8BrIb","part":{"id":"prt_e1f322b49001nVCUTykFLvoZZ5","messageID":"msg_e1f31c44d001nxtH9UuRl6CGIQ","sessionID":"ses_1e0ce95d2ffeVyPB3QV5a8BrIb","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a single predictor hypothesis: a tiny EX-updated BTB/BHT that predicts from stored targets instead of decoding branch immediates in IF, directly addressing the prior static predictor’s Fmax issue.","time":{"start":1778639842121,"end":1778639842265},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_078c237538655653016a03e3e201b48199883b50f563bb0bd2","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778639848487,"sessionID":"ses_1e0ce95d2ffeVyPB3QV5a8BrIb","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Ot9EdQNLpbu7j7vISeTaAE1Z","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r2s2\n+title: \"Tiny BTB branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core resolves every taken branch and jump in EX, so tight CoreMark\n+  loops pay a two-instruction redirect penalty on each taken iteration. The prior\n+  static backward predictor showed that avoiding these penalties can help CPI,\n+  but its IF-stage immediate decode and target add hurt Fmax enough to lose most\n+  of the gain.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small direct-mapped BTB with 2-bit saturating counters, updated only from\n+  resolved control-flow instructions in EX. IF predicts taken only on a valid tag\n+  hit with a taken counter and uses the stored target, otherwise it fetches pc+4;\n+  this keeps branch immediate decode and target addition out of the fetch path.\n+  Carry predicted next-PC metadata through IF/ID and ID/EX so EX redirects only\n+  when the stored prediction disagrees with the actual resolved next PC. This\n+  should recover most repeated loop-branch and unconditional jump penalties after\n+  warm-up with lower Fmax risk than the failed static predictor.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted next-PC and prediction-valid metadata to the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a small direct-mapped BTB/BHT lookup in IF, select stored targets on confident tag hits, and update entries from EX resolution signals.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch IF prediction metadata into ID/EX without changing raw instruction rs fields or RVFI-visible operands.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare predicted and actual next PC for branches and jumps, emit predictor update information, and redirect only on prediction mismatch.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire EX predictor update and misprediction redirect signals between ex_stage, if_stage, and the existing hazard logic.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r2s2\n+title: \"Tiny BTB branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core resolves every taken branch and jump in EX, so tight CoreMark\n+  loops pay a two-instruction redirect penalty on each taken iteration. The prior\n+  static backward predictor showed that avoiding these penalties can help CPI,\n+  but its IF-stage immediate decode and target add hurt Fmax enough to lose most\n+  of the gain.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small direct-mapped BTB with 2-bit saturating counters, updated only from\n+  resolved control-flow instructions in EX. IF predicts taken only on a valid tag\n+  hit with a taken counter and uses the stored target, otherwise it fetches pc+4;\n+  this keeps branch immediate decode and target addition out of the fetch path.\n+  Carry predicted next-PC metadata through IF/ID and ID/EX so EX redirects only\n+  when the stored prediction disagrees with the actual resolved next PC. This\n+  should recover most repeated loop-branch and unconditional jump penalties after\n+  warm-up with lower Fmax risk than the failed static predictor.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted next-PC and prediction-valid metadata to the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a small direct-mapped BTB/BHT lookup in IF, select stored targets on confident tag hits, and update entries from EX resolution signals.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch IF prediction metadata into ID/EX without changing raw instruction rs fields or RVFI-visible operands.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare predicted and actual next PC for branches and jumps, emit predictor update information, and redirect only on prediction mismatch.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire EX predictor update and misprediction redirect signals between ex_stage, if_stage, and the existing hazard logic.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r2s2\n+title: \"Tiny BTB branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  T