{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778650223646,"sessionID":"ses_1e0305f2affeEv6xCsIt4jmwx5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_pRjfzZ2TlFQmOWnibkp50pOA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r10s0\n+title: \"Use immediate sign for predictor update\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core depends on the one-entry registered lookahead predictor,\n+  but recent predictor variants regressed when they added IF-side compares,\n+  replacement state, or delayed promotion. A lower-risk micro-optimization is to\n+  keep the same single-entry predictor structure and useful direct-JAL training,\n+  while trimming EX-stage predictor-update control that is not architecturally\n+  visible.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  For conditional branches, replace the predictor update test\n+  `branch_target < in.pc` with the sign bit of the decoded B-immediate. On the\n+  bounded CoreMark address range, a negative B-immediate is exactly the loop-back\n+  case the predictor is trying to learn, and any rare wraparound distinction only\n+  affects speculative next-PC choice that EX already corrects. This removes a\n+  32-bit less-than comparator from the always-active EX predictor-update cone,\n+  preserves direct JAL updates that prior results showed are useful, and should\n+  improve Fmax without changing CPI on correctly predicted hot loops.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace branch_target < in.pc in pred_update_valid with the branch immediate sign bit, while leaving direct JAL updates, redirect correction, RVFI pc_next, and trap behavior unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto