{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778651668522,"sessionID":"ses_1e01b7558ffey1JQ9pYmA0GhMu","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_gk5ryFqkZC1FwSW2K2KIMs5N","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260513-001-r11s0\n2: title: \"Explicit signed compare datapath\"\n3: category: micro_opt\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The current best core already gained from simplifying the MEM byte-lane datapath, while most attempts that added predictor state, new side units, or broad control repacking regressed. A remaining low-risk hot cone is signed comparison in EX: SLT and BLT/BGE currently rely on generic signed less-than operators, which can infer full-width comparator/subtractor logic on the ALU and branch-resolution paths.\n6: hypothesis: |\n7:   Replace generic signed less-than comparisons with an explicit sign-bit fast path in both the ALU and branch comparator. For signed compares, when operand signs differ the result is just the left operand sign; when signs match, compare the low 31 bits as unsigned. This preserves exact RV32I SLT/BLT/BGE semantics, keeps the pipeline and predictor behavior unchanged, and may map to shallower LUT/carry logic on Tang Nano 20K for CoreMark's compare-heavy control flow.\n8: expected_impact:\n9:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n10:   confidence: medium\n11: changes:\n12:   - file: rtl/alu.sv\n13:     description: \"Implement ALU_SLT with explicit sign-bit handling and an unsigned low-bit compare instead of a generic signed less-than operator.\"\n14:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n15:     description: \"Share the same explicit signed-less-than predicate for BLT/BGE branch resolution while leaving unsigned/equality branches and redirect semantics unchanged.\"\n\n(End of file - total 15 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-001-r11s0\ntitle: \"Explicit signed compare datapath\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The current best core already gained from simplifying the MEM byte-lane datapath, while most attempts that added predictor state, new side units, or broad control repacking regressed. A remaining low-risk hot cone is signed comparison in EX: SLT and BLT/BGE currently rely on generic signed less-than operators, which can infer full-width comparator/subtractor logic on the ALU and branch-resolution paths.\nhypothesis: |\n  Replace generic signed less-than comparisons with an explicit sign-bit fast path in both the ALU and branch comparator. For signed compares, when operand signs differ the result is just the left operand sign; when signs match, compare the low 31 bits as unsigned. This preserves exact RV32I SLT/BLT/BGE semantics, keeps the pipeline and predictor behavior unchanged, and may map to shallower LUT/carry logic on Tang Nano 20K for CoreMark's compare-heavy control flow.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n    description: \"Implement ALU_SLT with explicit sign-bit handling and an unsigned low-bit compare instead of a generic signed less-than operator.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Share the same explicit signed-less-than predicate for BLT/BGE branch resolution while leaving unsigned/equality branches and redirect semantics unchanged.\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778651668516,"end":1778651668521}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f98db21693dbfe2016a04121413d48198b72dbe510f167655"}},"id":"prt_e1fe69f23001euUaEUwm16lvPq","sessionID":"ses_1e01b7558ffey1JQ9pYmA0GhMu","messageID":"msg_e1fe68b25001yrwcaJMm8lbMnp"}}
