ressure in the EX operand mux control, and avoids ever selecting a load effective address as forwarded rd data under unusual stall timing, without changing CPI or the RVFI retirement contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Drive the forward unit's EX/MEM write-enable input with a non-load producer predicate, leaving MEM/WB forwarding and hazard priorities unchanged.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Document or rename the EX/MEM forwarding input as a bypass-eligible producer so loads are excluded from the high-priority EX/MEM path without changing the two-bit select encoding.\"\n","additions":15,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778652375757,"end":1778652375761}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08ad02f0abd1c5c1016a0414d14a788198807f9db54819f57e"}},"id":"prt_e1ff1525c001ryWwXzZoQvFjlr","sessionID":"ses_1e00f9204ffeW3o4DkhsfmWwhG","messageID":"msg_e1ff0b80c001IhJ6vqSnxXkors"}}
