{"type":"text","timestamp":1778655823851,"sessionID":"ses_1dfdae821ffe0qfAq3dM5zxNpf","part":{"id":"prt_e2026070a001QKVPRQG7ewr6fs","messageID":"msg_e2025e738001Xl7wsQFOeHXI4w","sessionID":"ses_1dfdae821ffe0qfAq3dM5zxNpf","type":"text","text":"Writing the hypothesis YAML now with a single `rtl/mem_stage.sv` change and schema-safe fields.","time":{"start":1778655823626,"end":1778655823851},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_03905e84f8ce813c016a04224f5ee88198bd4bd85251c3158e","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778655831295,"sessionID":"ses_1dfdae821ffe0qfAq3dM5zxNpf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_yAzhtsY4MaRD7lp7dBs5v0Tb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r15s0\n+title: \"Isolate MEM word-load fast path\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The strongest successful micro-optimization simplified the MEM byte-lane\n+  datapath, while most broader control, forwarding, ALU, and predictor changes\n+  regressed. The current MEM stage still computes byte and halfword extraction\n+  logic from dmem_rdata on every cycle, even though CoreMark's hottest memory\n+  operations are likely aligned word loads and stores. Keeping the proven case\n+  mux discipline but isolating the word-load path may trim dmem_rdata fanout\n+  and preserve Fmax without changing CPI or pipeline control.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure mem_stage load-data generation so aligned word loads take a\n+  direct dmem_rdata path, while byte and halfword lane extraction is only in\n+  the narrow-width arms. Leave the existing byte-mask generation,\n+  misalignment trap detection, dmem gating, RVFI aligned-memory reporting, and\n+  MEM/WB timing unchanged. This should give synthesis a cleaner fast path for\n+  the common LW case and avoid reintroducing the failed halfword special-case\n+  or EX precompute control costs.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Restructure load_data so word loads bypass byte/half extraction logic directly, while preserving the existing masks, traps, RVFI fields, and pipeline timing.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,25 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r15s0\n+title: \"Isolate MEM word-load fast path\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The strongest successful micro-optimization simplified the MEM byte-lane\n+  datapath, while most broader control, forwarding, ALU, and predictor changes\n+  regressed. The current MEM stage still computes byte and halfword extraction\n+  logic from dmem_rdata on every cycle, even though CoreMark's hottest memory\n+  operations are likely aligned word loads and stores. Keeping the proven case\n+  mux discipline but isolating the word-load path may trim dmem_rdata fanout\n+  and preserve Fmax without changing CPI or pipeline control.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure mem_stage load-data generation so aligned word loads take a\n+  direct dmem_rdata path, while byte and halfword lane extraction is only in\n+  the narrow-width arms. Leave the existing byte-mask generation,\n+  misalignment trap detection, dmem gating, RVFI aligned-memory reporting, and\n+  MEM/WB timing unchanged. This should give synthesis a cleaner fast path for\n+  the common LW case and avoid reintroducing the failed halfword special-case\n+  or EX precompute control costs.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Restructure load_data so word loads bypass byte/half extraction logic directly, while preserving the existing masks, traps, RVFI fields, and pipeline timing.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.cl