im still see the same architectural source metadata; only the interlock predicate changes.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add IF/ID rs1_used and rs2_used inputs and apply them to the load-use dependency comparisons without changing other stall, flush, or hold priorities.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Derive compact source-use predicates from the IF/ID instruction opcode/funct class and pass them to the hazard unit while preserving all existing pipeline and RVFI source fields.\"\n","additions":15,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778641972988,"end":1778641972992}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03117b5830e69f29016a03ec30000c81988c824fe25906819f"}},"id":"prt_e1f529be6001C6OPmQSq495os0","sessionID":"ses_1e0adc588ffeVKNLv0lCU4xwyI","messageID":"msg_e1f52659e0012SC3NkyEln2vkl"}}
