{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778642949653,"sessionID":"ses_1e09f880cffeyiMxf2zar7Oac0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Ehc2e4zYyoFp48ddMHpLiBrT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r4s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r4s0\n+title: \"Case-based MEM byte-lane muxes\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core already gained by removing rare DIV/REM from the common\n+  EX datapath, while recent front-end and multiplier micro-optimizations lost\n+  Fmax. A lower-risk remaining hot path is the MEM/WB load-data and store-mask\n+  logic: CoreMark is load/store heavy, and the current MEM stage uses variable\n+  shifts for byte extraction and byte-lane mask generation in the same cycle\n+  that load data can feed writeback and forwarding.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the MEM-stage variable shifts with explicit case muxes indexed by\n+  address bits. Generate byte and halfword load slices directly from\n+  dmem_rdata[7:0], [15:8], [23:16], and [31:24], and generate store masks from\n+  width/address case arms rather than left-shifting a constant. This should map\n+  to smaller LUT mux trees on Tang Nano 20K, shorten the dmem_rdata-to-WB and\n+  address-to-mask paths, and preserve the exact RVFI aligned-memory reporting,\n+  misalignment traps, and pipeline timing.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Rewrite byte/halfword load extraction and store byte-mask generation as explicit case muxes instead of variable shifts, leaving misalignment gating and RVFI fields unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r4s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tou