{"type":"text","timestamp":1778645901274,"sessionID":"ses_1e07258dcffeQK1ey74mC0TKeo","part":{"id":"prt_e1f8e9f80001yvlvzr4MrXNkS7","messageID":"msg_e1f8dd479001pChnmkx8Jcb5EG","sessionID":"ses_1e07258dcffeQK1ey74mC0TKeo","type":"text","text":"The prior successful micro-opt was a MEM-stage datapath simplification; recent arithmetic, predictor, source-use, and reset cleanups regressed. I’m selecting a lower-risk control-path pruning hypothesis: narrow dead pipeline control fields after EX/MEM and MEM/WB to reduce flop/mux/routing pressure without changing CPI or the external contract.","time":{"start":1778645901184,"end":1778645901272},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_020ab48c285a76b4016a03fb8cdc548199b933321f3ebbc6f5","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778645910905,"sessionID":"ses_1e07258dcffeQK1ey74mC0TKeo","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_bIKlgSZZpTsq5TmnReoVa6Zt","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Prune late pipeline control fields\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent attempts show that adding front-end prediction or arithmetic side-control tends to cost more Fmax than it saves, while the successful MEM-stage case-mux change improved fitness by simplifying always-active datapaths. The current pipeline still carries the full decoded ctrl_t through EX/MEM and MEM/WB even though many fields are dead after EX, and almost all fields are dead after MEM. Those unnecessary bits add flops, reset/hold muxing, struct routing, and fanout on hot writeback and forwarding control.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split the late pipeline control payload into narrower MEM-stage and WB-stage control structs. EX/MEM only needs memory access width/sign, mem read/write, reg_write, mem_to_reg, and trap state; MEM/WB only needs reg_write, mem_to_reg, and trap state because RVFI memory masks/data have already been materialized. Removing unused branch, jump, ALU-op, operand-select, AUIPC/LUI, and memory-format bits from late pipeline registers should reduce Tang Nano 20K placement/routing pressure and shorten small but always-active control muxes without changing instruction timing, RVFI fields, or CoreMark CPI.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add narrow ex_mem and mem_wb control typedefs, change ex_mem_t and mem_wb_t to use them, and drop unused late-stage control fields such as is_lui after decode.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Populate the narrowed EX/MEM control payload from the decoded control signals after branch/jump/misalignment handling while preserving redirect and RVFI pc_next behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Consume only the narrowed memory control fields and emit a minimal WB control payload containing reg_write, mem_to_reg, and is_illegal.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the minimal MEM/WB control payload for writeback enable and result selection without changing rd_wdata semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Update hazard, forwarding, RVFI trap, and rd_wen references to the narrowed late-stage control fields while preserving the nret=1 top-level interface.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Prune late pipeline control fields\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent attempts show that adding front-end prediction or arithmetic side-control tends to cost more Fmax than it saves, while the successful MEM-stage case-mux change improved fitness by simplifying always-active datapaths. The current pipeline still carries the full decoded ctrl_t through EX/MEM and MEM/WB even though many fields are dead after EX, and almost all fields are dead after MEM. Those unnecessary bits add flops, reset/hold muxing, struct routing, and fanout on hot writeback and forwarding control.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split the late pipeline control payload into narrower MEM-stage and WB-stage control structs. EX/MEM only needs memory access width/sign, mem read/write, reg_write, mem_to_reg, and trap state; MEM/WB only needs reg_write, mem_to_reg, and trap state because RVFI memory masks/data have already been materialized. Removing unused branch, jump, ALU-op, operand-select, AUIPC/LUI, and memory-format bits from late pipeline registers should reduce Tang Nano 20K placement/routing pressure and shorten small but always-active control muxes without changing instruction timing, RVFI fields, or CoreMark CPI.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add narrow ex_mem and mem_wb control typedefs, change ex_mem_t and mem_wb_t to use them, and drop unused late-stage control fields such as is_lui after decode.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Populate the narrowed EX/MEM control payload from the decoded control signals after branch/jump/misalignment handling while preserving redirect and RVFI pc_next behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Consume only the narrowed memory control fields and emit a minimal WB control payload containing reg_write, mem_to_reg, and is_illegal.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the minimal MEM/WB control payload for writeback enable and result selection without changing rd_wdata semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Update hazard, forwarding, RVFI trap, and rd_wen references to the narrowed late-stage control fields while preserving the nret=1 top-level interface.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Inde