{"type":"text","timestamp":1778646585596,"sessionID":"ses_1e0674d53ffeBo2G1UgS6x2zUG","part":{"id":"prt_e1f991006001bQ1a2OAnuvQzVm","messageID":"msg_e1f98d4c20019xNcXkSAw5jpMS","sessionID":"ses_1e0674d53ffeBo2G1UgS6x2zUG","type":"text","text":"The prior `micro_opt` history points away from new prediction paths, load-use source decoding, late-control pruning, and multiplier restructuring. The strongest contained angle is simplifying always-active operand forwarding comparisons/muxing without changing pipeline timing or RVFI.","time":{"start":1778646585350,"end":1778646585595},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_02884dfde43c1fef016a03fe393fb48199b964f454acda6468","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778646636640,"sessionID":"ses_1e0674d53ffeBo2G1UgS6x2zUG","part":{"id":"prt_e1f99d7b8001VYcuWpIVN9HAK0","messageID":"msg_e1f98d4c20019xNcXkSAw5jpMS","sessionID":"ses_1e0674d53ffeBo2G1UgS6x2zUG","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a focused hypothesis that removes dead EX/MEM branch metadata, rather than adding a new predictor or changing arithmetic. It is intentionally small: branch resolution already happens entirely in EX, and the latched `branch_taken`/`branch_target` fields are not consumed downstream.","time":{"start":1778646636472,"end":1778646636639},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_02884dfde43c1fef016a03fe6c6094819995bdeca0bcdb68cd","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778646640945,"sessionID":"ses_1e0674d53ffeBo2G1UgS6x2zUG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_3UemAxJnUJHFHfkZ3OFj0KYN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r7s0\n+title: \"Drop dead branch payload\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent micro-optimization attempts show that added front-end logic, broad\n+  control repacking, and multiplier restructuring tend to lose Fmax, while\n+  targeted removal or simplification of always-carried datapath logic is the\n+  safer path. In the current bench core, branch resolution is fully completed\n+  inside EX: redirect, predictor update, pc_next, and trap handling are all\n+  produced before the EX/MEM register. The EX/MEM payload still carries\n+  branch_taken and branch_target even though MEM, WB, RVFI, forwarding, and\n+  hazard logic do not consume them.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove the unused branch_taken and branch_target fields from ex_mem_t and\n+  delete the corresponding EX-stage register assignments. This should reduce\n+  the EX/MEM register by 33 bits, including reset and dmem-stall hold muxing,\n+  without changing instruction timing, branch redirect behavior, predictor\n+  updates, RVFI pc_wdata, trap behavior, or CoreMark CPI. The change is much\n+  narrower than the prior late-control pruning attempt: it only deletes fields\n+  already proven dead downstream, avoiding new packed-control structs or extra\n+  muxing on hot paths.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the unused branch_taken and branch_target members from ex_mem_t while leaving pc_next and all RVFI-relevant fields intact.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Delete the EX/MEM register assignments for the removed branch metadata; keep redirect, predictor update, and pc_next resolution unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r7s0\n+title: \"Drop dead branch payload\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent micro-optimization attempts show that added front-end logic, broad\n+  control repacking, and multiplier restructuring tend to lose Fmax, while\n+  targeted removal or simplification of always-carried datapath logic is the\n+  safer path. In the current bench core, branch resolution is fully completed\n+  inside EX: redirect, predictor update, pc_next, and trap handling are all\n+  produced before the EX/MEM register. The EX/MEM payload still carries\n+  branch_taken and branch_target even though MEM, WB, RVFI, forwarding, and\n+  hazard logic do not consume them.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove the unused branch_taken and branch_target fields from ex_mem_t and\n+  delete the corresponding EX-stage register assignments. This should reduce\n+  the EX/MEM register by 33 bits, including reset and dmem-stall hold muxing,\n+  without changing instruction timing, branch redirect behavior, predictor\n+  updates, RVFI pc_wdata, trap behavior, or CoreMark CPI. The change is much\n+  narrower than the prior late-control pruning attempt: it only deletes fields\n+  already proven dead downstream, avoiding new packed-control structs or extra\n+  muxin