{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778651541188,"sessionID":"ses_1e01b787affeYBsFmVLRwx351W","part":{"id":"prt_e1fe4aec3001noXgHZ92hsi0W0","messageID":"msg_e1fe4a9ed001RIHu2K1NXA0q6q","sessionID":"ses_1e01b787affeYBsFmVLRwx351W","snapshot":"fda0ea5844944cc81b52a6b6f9989385bf5dadf2","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778651554416,"sessionID":"ses_1e01b787affeYBsFmVLRwx351W","part":{"id":"prt_e1fe4e1d0001Ij1B7MDEEResCo","messageID":"msg_e1fe4a9ed001RIHu2K1NXA0q6q","sessionID":"ses_1e01b787affeYBsFmVLRwx351W","type":"text","text":"Structural history is dominated by failed front-end buffering, IF/ID retiming, MEM descriptor precompute, store buffering, and multiplier side units. The least-overlapped remaining structural angle is to reduce active branch/ALU comparator depth in EX without adding front-end prediction state or memory-order machinery.","time":{"start":1778651554256,"end":1778651554416},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_008bd17edf97b25f016a0411a22a98819a943a408826004229","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778651563390,"sessionID":"ses_1e01b787affeYBsFmVLRwx351W","part":{"id":"prt_e1fe5047f001ok3PqbvuIK1mr5","messageID":"msg_e1fe4a9ed001RIHu2K1NXA0q6q","sessionID":"ses_1e01b787affeYBsFmVLRwx351W","type":"text","text":"Writing the hypothesis file now, focused on a no-CPI EX-stage structural split: isolate branch condition evaluation into a compact subtract/flag unit instead of parallel generic comparators inside `ex_stage.sv`.","time":{"start":1778651563135,"end":1778651563389},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_008bd17edf97b25f016a0411ab0d94819a9390081837344c1a","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778651570219,"sessionID":"ses_1e01b787affeYBsFmVLRwx351W","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_hbuXhH6BRCFjC5GmyiUXx3Or","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r11s1\n+title: \"Compact EX branch comparator unit\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core already recovered useful CoreMark IPC with the registered\n+  hot-edge predictor, so the next structural opportunity should preserve that\n+  behavior while reducing the EX redirect path. ex_stage currently builds branch\n+  equality, signed less-than, unsigned less-than, greater/equal variants, target\n+  selection, misalignment handling, and ALU result muxing in one large block.\n+  Prior front-end queues, IF/ID retiming, store buffers, and multiplier side\n+  units mostly lost because they added control or CPI cost; a local EX compare\n+  reshaping has no new stalls and avoids touching the fetch predictor policy.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split branch condition evaluation out of ex_stage into a small branch_unit that\n+  computes BEQ/BNE/BLT/BGE/BLTU/BGEU from one equality check and one subtractor\n+  flag path. Use sign-bit aware subtract flags for signed and unsigned ordering\n+  instead of inferring several parallel 32-bit comparators in the EX stage case\n+  statement. Keep branch_target, jump_target, misalignment trap behavior, RVFI\n+  pc_wdata, and predictor updates semantically unchanged. This should shorten\n+  the branch-resolve/control cone and improve Fmax without changing nret, memory\n+  timing, predictor capacity, or CoreMark CPI.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/branch_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a compact combinational branch comparator using equality plus subtract-derived signed/unsigned ordering flags.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the inline branch_cond comparator case with branch_unit output while preserving redirect, trap, predictor-update, and RVFI pc_next behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r11s1\n+title: \"Compact EX branch comparator unit\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core already recovered useful CoreMark IPC with the registered\n+  hot-edge predictor, so the next structural opportunity should preserve that\n+  behavior while reducing the EX redirect path. ex_stage currently builds branch\n+  equality, signed less-than, unsigned less-than, greater/equal variants, target\n+  selection, misalignment handling, and ALU result muxing in one large block.\n+  Prior front-end queues, IF/ID retiming, store buffers, and multiplier side\n+  units mostly lost because they added control or CPI cost; a local EX compare\n+  reshaping has no new stalls and avoids touching the fetch predictor policy.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split branch condition evaluation out of ex_stage into a small branch_unit that\n+  computes BEQ/BNE/BLT/BGE/BLTU/BGEU from one equality check and one subtractor\n+  flag path. Use sign-bit aware subtract flags for signed and unsigned ordering\n+  instead of inferring several parallel 32-bit comparators in the EX stage case\n+  statement. Keep branch_target, jump_target, misalignment trap behavior, RVFI\n+  pc_wdata, and predictor updates semantically unchanged. This should shorten\n+  the branch-resolve/control cone and improve Fmax without changing nret, memory\n+  timing, predictor capacity, or CoreMark CPI.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/branch_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a compact combinational branch comparator using equality plus subtract-derived signed/unsigned ordering flags.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the inline branch_cond comparator case with branch_unit output while preserving redirect, trap, predictor-update, and RVFI pc_next behavior.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r11s1\n+title: \"Compact EX branch comparator unit\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core already recovered useful CoreMark IPC with the registered\n+  hot-edge predictor, so the next structural opportunity should preserve that\n+  behavior while reducing the EX redirect path. ex_stage currently builds branch\n+  equality, signed less-than, unsigned less-than, greater/equal variants, target\n+  selection, misalignment handling, and ALU result muxing in one large block.\n+  Prior front-end queues, IF/ID retiming, store buffers, and multiplier side\n+  units mostly lost because they added control or CPI cost; a local EX compare\n+  reshaping has no new stalls and avoids touching the fetch predictor policy.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split branch condition evaluation out of ex_stage into a small branch_unit that\n+  computes BEQ/BNE/BLT/BGE/BLTU/BGEU from one equality check and one subtractor\n+  flag path. Use sign-bit aware subtract flags for signed and unsigned ordering\n+  instead of inferring several parallel 32-bit comparators in the EX stage case\n+  statement. Keep branch_target, jump_target, misalignment trap behavior, RVFI\n+  pc_wdata, and predictor updates semantically unchanged. This should shorten\n+  the branch-resolve/control cone and improve Fmax without changing nret, memory\n+  timing, predictor capacity, or CoreMark CPI.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/branch_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a compact combinational branch comparator using equality plus subtract-derived signed/unsigned ordering flags.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the inline branch_cond comparator case with branch_unit output while preserving redirect, trap, predictor-update, and RVFI pc_next behavior.\"\n","additions":29,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778651570217,"end":1778651570219}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_008bd17edf97b25f016a0411ab4f90819aa510844deed726c8"}},"id":"prt_e1fe5057e0017sVNJEFCfQRa9m","sessionID":"ses_1e01b787affeYBsFmVLRwx351W","messageID":"msg_e1fe4a9ed001RIHu2K1NXA0q6q"}}
