{"type":"text","timestamp":1778652337819,"sessionID":"ses_1e00f926bffeF2M6IVSYypxS0S","part":{"id":"prt_e1ff0d5b9001w7q3MwnSinQtAI","messageID":"msg_e1ff0a18a001isUcx5xPXAVUHy","sessionID":"ses_1e00f926bffeF2M6IVSYypxS0S","type":"text","text":"The prior structural slot has already tried front-end buffering/IF retiming, store buffering, load-data bypassing, PC-relative retiming, multiplier side units, and branch-unit factoring. I’m going to avoid those patterns and focus the hypothesis on a narrower retiming: register only the long RVFI-only MEM payload so CoreMark’s active writeback/forwarding path carries a smaller hot register.","time":{"start":1778652337593,"end":1778652337818},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0243e61284b1ab97016a0414b17978819abac863fefe83cdcd","phase":"commentary"}}}}
