{"type":"text","timestamp":1778652423467,"sessionID":"ses_1e00f926bffeF2M6IVSYypxS0S","part":{"id":"prt_e1ff22346001vFcL8vGqhcCk50","messageID":"msg_e1ff0d7f40015fcnXn4rP6FLVg","sessionID":"ses_1e00f926bffeF2M6IVSYypxS0S","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a structural hypothesis for a registered writeback result path. The goal is to remove the MEM/WB `mem_to_reg` mux from the forwarding and regfile-write critical path without changing pipeline depth, stalls, prediction, RVFI ordering, or memory behavior.","time":{"start":1778652422982,"end":1778652423466},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_03126e8c2d1822f6016a041506aa2c819a9740282e57324a41","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778652430518,"sessionID":"ses_1e00f926bffeF2M6IVSYypxS0S","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_EwD3YeGaa5Vng3XeIJdTWKbk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r12s1\n+title: \"Register writeback result\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current MEM/WB stage still computes the final writeback value with a\n+  combinational mem_to_reg mux in wb_stage. That mux feeds both the regfile\n+  write port and the MEM/WB-to-EX forwarding path, so dependent CoreMark\n+  instructions can see an active path from the MEM/WB register through the\n+  writeback mux, EX operand mux, ALU, and EX/MEM register. Prior structural\n+  attempts that changed fetch policy, store buffering, branch factoring, or\n+  M-extension latency often paid control or CPI costs; this is a narrower\n+  retiming of an existing datapath with no new stalls.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Precompute and register the final rd writeback data at the MEM/WB boundary.\n+  mem_stage should latch a wb_data field equal to load_data for loads and\n+  alu_result for non-load register writes, while preserving the existing\n+  read_data, alu_result, RVFI memory fields, and hold_wb behavior. wb_stage\n+  can then drive w_data directly from the registered wb_data field instead of\n+  selecting between read_data and alu_result every cycle. This should shorten\n+  the hot MEM/WB forwarding and regfile-write path without changing nret=1,\n+  RVFI rd_wdata semantics, load/store timing, predictor behavior, or CoreMark\n+  iterations per instruction.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a registered wb_data field to mem_wb_t while keeping the existing RVFI-visible alu_result and read_data fields intact.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch wb_data alongside the existing MEM/WB payload, selecting load_data for mem_to_reg cases and alu_result otherwise, and retain it during hold_wb just like the other forwarding fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drive w_data from the registered wb_data field so the MEM/WB-to-EX forwarding path no longer includes the combinational mem_to_reg result mux.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r12s1\n+title: \"Register writeback result\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current MEM/WB stage still computes the final writeback value with a\n+  combinational mem_to_reg mux in wb_stage. That mux feeds both the regfile\n+  write port and the MEM/WB-to-EX forwarding path, so dependent CoreMark\n+  instructions can see an active path from the MEM/WB register through the\n+  writeback mux, EX operand mux, ALU, and EX/MEM register. Prior structural\n+  attempts that changed fetch policy, store buffering, branch factoring, or\n+  M-extension latency often paid control or CPI costs; this is a narrower\n+  retiming of an existing datapath with no new stalls.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Precompute and register the final rd writeback data at the MEM/WB boundary.\n+  mem_stage should latch a wb_data field equal to load_data for loads and\n+  alu_result for non-load register writes, while pr