{"type":"text","timestamp":1778654593991,"sessionID":"ses_1dfee922fffeqMxUWMHticeL0j","part":{"id":"prt_e20134304001hGP0657FBsPZ1r","messageID":"msg_e2012c7b4001cHkzU52mNXbjrP","sessionID":"ses_1dfee922fffeqMxUWMHticeL0j","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as a one-cycle registered multiply sidecar: it removes all real multiplier logic from the common ALU/branch/load EX cone without repeating the failed long-latency MUL side-unit tradeoff.","time":{"start":1778654593796,"end":1778654593990},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0af169925af1a16d016a041d81b3b88199a99f20870daddbfa","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778654600050,"sessionID":"ses_1dfee922fffeqMxUWMHticeL0j","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_SCGV4kFMPKAEj4Vi7E8r18JE","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r14s1\n+title: \"One-cycle registered multiply sidecar\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage still carries three real 32x32 multiply products through\n+  the common combinational ALU result path. Prior high-half-only and long-latency\n+  all-MUL side units regressed: the former left low-half MUL on the hot path,\n+  while the latter paid too much CoreMark CPI on ordinary MUL instructions.\n+  A narrower structural split can remove multiplier logic from the normal\n+  integer/branch/load/store cone while keeping multiply latency to one extra\n+  cycle instead of an iterative stall.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a registered one-cycle multiply sidecar in EX for MUL, MULH, MULHU, and\n+  MULHSU. On a real M-extension multiply, EX captures the forwarded operands\n+  and opcode into a small mul_unit, emits a single bubble into EX/MEM, then\n+  consumes the registered result on the next cycle using the existing ex_busy\n+  stall path. In non-ALTOPS builds, alu.sv no longer computes real multiplier\n+  products; in RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS builds, keep the current algebraic stand-ins\n+  in the ALU so formal remains tractable. This should improve Fmax by removing\n+  multiplier fanout and wide M-result muxing from the common EX cone while\n+  limiting CoreMark IPC loss to one cycle per multiply.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real non-ALTOPS MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU product logic from the normal ALU path while preserving ALTOPS substitutions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a small registered one-cycle RV32M multiply sidecar that computes all four multiply variants with RV32IM-correct signedness.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect multiply operations, launch the sidecar, emit one EX/MEM bubble while the registered result is produced, and write the sidecar result into the retiring instruction.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Move or extend multiplier correctness coverage so the new sidecar, not the stripped ALU path, is checked against the existing RV32M vectors.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r14s1\n+title: \"One-cycle registered multiply sidecar\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage still carries three real 32x32 multiply products through\n+  the common combinational ALU result path. Prior high-half-only and long-latency\n+  all-MUL side units regressed: the former left low-half MUL on the hot path,\n+  while the latter paid too much CoreMark CPI on ordinary MUL instructions.\n+  A narrower structural split can remove multiplier logic from the normal\n+  integer/branch/load/store cone while keeping multiply latency to one extra\n+  cycle instead of an iterative stall.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a registered one-cycle multiply sidecar in EX for MUL, MULH, MULHU, and\n+  MULHSU. On a real M-extension multiply, EX captures the forwarded operands\n+  and opcode into a small mul_unit, emits a single bubble into EX/MEM, then\n+  consumes the registered result on the next cycle using the existing ex_busy\n+  stall path. In non-ALTOPS builds, alu.sv no longer computes real multiplier\n+  products; in RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS builds, keep the current algebraic stand-ins\n+  in the ALU so formal remains tractable. This should improve Fmax by removing\n+  multiplier fanout and wide M-result muxing from the common EX cone while\n+  limiting CoreMark IPC loss to one cycle per multiply.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real non-ALTOPS MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU product logic from the normal ALU path while preserving ALTOPS substitutions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a small registered one-cycle RV32M multiply sidecar that computes all four multiply variants with RV32IM-correct signedness.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect multiply operations, launch the sidecar, emit one EX/MEM bubble while the registered result is produced, and write the sidecar result into the retiring instruction.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Move or extend multiplier correctness coverage so the new sidecar, not the stripped ALU path, is checked against the existing RV32M vectors.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r14s1\n+title: \"One-cycle registered multiply sidecar\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage still carries three real 32x32 multiply products through\n+  the common combinational ALU result path. Prior high-half-only and long-latency\n+  all-MUL side units regressed: the former left low-half MUL on the hot path,\n+  while the latter paid too much CoreMark CPI on ordinary MUL instructions.\n+  A narrower structural split can remove multiplier logic from the normal\n+  integer/branch/load/store cone while keeping multiply latency to one extra\n+  cycle instead of an iterative stall.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a registered one-cycle multiply sidecar in EX for MUL, MULH, MULHU, and\n+  MULHSU. On a real M-extension multiply, EX captures the forwarded operands\n+  and opcode into a small mul_unit, emits a single bubble into EX/MEM, then\n+  consumes the registered result on the next cycle using the existing ex_busy\n+  stall path. In non-ALTOPS builds, alu.sv no longer computes real multiplier\n+  products; in RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS builds, keep the current algebraic stand-ins\n+  in the ALU so formal remains tractable. This should improve Fmax by removing\n+  multiplier fanout and wide M-result muxing from the common EX cone while\n+  limiting CoreMark IPC loss to one cycle per multiply.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real non-ALTOPS MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU product logic from the normal ALU path while preserving ALTOPS substitutions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a small registered one-cycle RV32M multiply sidecar that computes all four multiply variants with RV32IM-correct signedness.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect multiply operations, launch the sidecar, emit one EX/MEM bubble while the registered result is produced, and write the sidecar result into the retiring instruction.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Move or extend multiplier correctness coverage so the new sidecar, not the stripped ALU path, is checked against the existing RV32M vectors.\"\n","additions":33,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778654600047,"end":1778654600050}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0af169925af1a16d016a041d81e47c81998682fe9492a3834b"}},"id":"prt_e201343ca001EyaSrZYPI448mI","sessionID":"ses_1dfee922fffeqMxUWMHticeL0j","messageID":"msg_e2012c7b4001cHkzU52mNXbjrP"}}
