{"type":"text","timestamp":1778641977011,"sessionID":"ses_1e0adc4a6ffeJt5GhOClgitqS3","part":{"id":"prt_e1f52bcf0001S05740pRsvdNVX","messageID":"msg_e1f5263b5001lQQKBxSgujfq3M","sessionID":"ses_1e0adc4a6ffeJt5GhOClgitqS3","type":"text","text":"The relevant negative structural attempt was the two-entry fetch skid buffer; it regressed from extra queue control. I’m going to write a narrower structural-retiming hypothesis: add a single registered IF/ID boundary to break the imem-to-decode/regfile path without fetch-ahead queue logic.","time":{"start":1778641976560,"end":1778641977010},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_046c735d87eeb337016a03ec385ee0819bb2c3cb3aaca70ddc","phase":"commentary"}}}}
