{"type":"text","timestamp":1778642913408,"sessionID":"ses_1e09f8876ffe9aqIZzQ4X2m5ie","part":{"id":"prt_e1f60fe9c001HBRWYiv1YnSEkn","messageID":"msg_e1f609dfe002BVYe2GGXzWdEo1","sessionID":"ses_1e09f8876ffe9aqIZzQ4X2m5ie","type":"text","text":"The prior structural wins came from removing rare DIV/REM from the common EX path; later front-end buffering/retiming regressed. I’m going to propose a similarly selective structural decoupling: keep common low-half `MUL` single-cycle, but move rare high-half multiply variants off the always-on ALU path so CoreMark pays little CPI cost while timing sees fewer parallel multiplier/mux inputs.","time":{"start":1778642910876,"end":1778642913406},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_04218ed7d0bc271c016a03efdec530819b8bc59a03adaa0771","phase":"commentary"}}}}
