{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778642936153,"sessionID":"ses_1e09f8876ffe9aqIZzQ4X2m5ie","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_jdXm2kzHBQG7HbfaWCe7croM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Iterative high-half multiply side unit\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful DIV/REM side-unit hypothesis showed that this FPGA benefits\n+  when rare, wide arithmetic is removed from the common EX-stage ALU result\n+  path. The current ALU still computes three 64-bit multiply variants every\n+  cycle and muxes their high halves alongside the common RV32I and low-half\n+  MUL operations. CoreMark should mostly exercise ordinary integer ops and\n+  low-half MUL, while MULH/MULHU/MULHSU are uncommon in compiler output.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep ALU_MUL as a single-cycle low-half multiply, but move ALU_MULH,\n+  ALU_MULHU, and ALU_MULHSU into a small multi-cycle high-multiply side unit\n+  owned by EX, using the same stall/consume pattern already proven for DIV/REM.\n+  The common ALU path then only needs the low-half unsigned product for MUL and\n+  no longer carries signed high-product result muxing on every instruction.\n+  Rare high-half multiply instructions pay a short structural stall, but the\n+  expected CoreMark mix should recover more Fmax than it loses in IPC.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real ALU_MULH, ALU_MULHU, and ALU_MULHSU product logic from the normal combinational ALU path while preserving RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect high-half multiply operations, start a small side unit, stall EX until the result is ready, and route the completed result through the existing EX/MEM retirement path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add any compact side-unit operation encoding or pipeline metadata needed to distinguish signed, unsigned, and signed-unsigned high-half multiply results.\"\n+  - file: rtl/high_mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a dedicated multi-cycle high-half multiply helper for MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU with RV32M-correct signedness behavior.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or preserve high-half multiply vectors so the side-unit implementation remains covered for signed, unsigned, and mixed-signed corner cases.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Iterative high-half multiply side unit\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful DIV/REM side-unit hypothesis showed that this FPGA benefits\n+  when rare, wide arithmetic is removed from the common EX-stage ALU result\n+  path. The current ALU still computes three 64-bit multiply variants every\n+  cycle and muxes their high halves alongside the common RV32I and low-half\n+  MUL operations. CoreMark should mostly exercise ordinary integer ops and\n+  low-half MUL, while MULH/MULHU/MULHSU are uncommon in compiler output.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep ALU_MUL as a single-cycle low-half multiply, but move ALU_MULH,\n+  ALU_MULHU, and ALU_MULHSU into a small multi-cycle high-multiply side unit\n+  owned by EX, using the same stall/consume pattern already proven for DIV/REM.\n+  The common ALU path then only needs the low-half unsigned product for MUL and\n+  no longer carries signed high-product result muxing on every instruction.\n+  Rare high-half multiply instructions pay a short structural stall, but the\n+  expected CoreMark mix should recover more Fmax than it loses in IPC.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real ALU_MULH, ALU_MULHU, and ALU_MULHSU product logic from the normal combinational ALU path while preserving RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect high-half multiply operations, start a small side unit, stall EX until the result is ready, and route the completed result through the existing EX/MEM retirement path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add any compact side-unit operation encoding or pipeline metadata needed to distinguish signed, unsigned, and signed-unsigned high-half multiply results.\"\n+  - file: rtl/high_mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a dedicated multi-cycle high-half multiply helper for MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU with RV32M-correct signedness behavior.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or preserve high-half multiply vectors so the side-unit implementation remains covered for signed, unsigned, and mixed-signed corner cases.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tourna