es MEM and dmem is not ready, capture its address, replicated write data, and byte mask, allow the store to retire through MEM/WB, and keep driving the buffered write until the bus accepts it. While the buffer is occupied, stall only younger LOAD/STORE instructions to preserve memory ordering and the single dmem port; let younger non-memory instructions continue. Do not buffer UART or timing-marker MMIO stores so CoreMark brackets and output ordering remain exact. This should hide a fraction of random store backpressure cycles without changing nret, branch behavior, or common EX timing.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 6, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/mem_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a one... (line truncated to 2000 chars)","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","time":{"start":1778645857476,"end":1778645857481}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_041676c2cd4cc29f016a03fb610e68819b890c429a1a086fb3"}},"id":"prt_e1f8df386002DDGQ7wlKz6E8hH","sessionID":"ses_1e0725802ffe3aQNSWn12Om6z3","messageID":"msg_e1f8de58f001Q3vZ04SXiihHdj"}}
