{"type":"text","timestamp":1778645908305,"sessionID":"ses_1e0725802ffe3aQNSWn12Om6z3","part":{"id":"prt_e1f8eb8a6001hJU6am3DX8T1n4","messageID":"msg_e1f8eb3ad0017PIP7V7YZoEDi3","sessionID":"ses_1e0725802ffe3aQNSWn12Om6z3","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis file now with short `rtl/...` paths and `category: structural` as required.","time":{"start":1778645907622,"end":1778645908303},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_01aa2b619cbeebe4016a03fb938a2881989789957b74c761b2","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778645919426,"sessionID":"ses_1e0725802ffe3aQNSWn12Om6z3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_jqiznG9d7XA4ZPCKjtK2HU5h","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r6s1\n+title: \"MEM load-data bypass to EX\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage pipeline always injects a bubble for a load-use pair,\n+  even when the data memory is ready and the load data is available during the\n+  following MEM cycle. CoreMark is load/store heavy, and the recent MEM-stage\n+  byte-lane improvement indicates this benchmark is sensitive to the memory\n+  datapath. Prior structural frontend decoupling and prediction attempts paid\n+  too much fetch-path timing cost, so a backend bypass is a more focused IPC\n+  improvement.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a direct MEM-stage load-result bypass into the EX operand forwarding\n+  network. When a load sits in EX/MEM and a younger instruction in ID/EX reads\n+  the same rd, EX should use the current MEM load_data instead of stalling for\n+  the value to reach MEM/WB. The bypass must be disabled for misaligned/trapping\n+  loads so dependent instructions retain the old architectural register value,\n+  and dmem backpressure should still freeze the pipeline until valid load data\n+  is available. This removes the normal one-cycle load-use penalty without\n+  adding branch prediction, fetch queues, or nret changes.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose the combinational aligned load_data value and a bypass-valid signal gated off for misaligned or trapping loads.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a MEM-load forwarding input and select it for rs1/rs2 operands ahead of the older MEM/WB path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Teach forwarding to distinguish EX/MEM ALU-result forwarding from EX/MEM load-data bypass forwarding.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the unconditional load-use bubble when the new MEM-to-EX bypass can safely satisfy the dependency, while preserving stalls under dmem backpressure.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the MEM-stage bypass value and valid signal into the forwarding and EX-stage operand paths.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r6s1\n+title: \"MEM load-data bypass to EX\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage pipeline always injects a bubble for a load-use pair,\n+  even when the data memory is ready and the load data is available during the\n+  following MEM cycle. CoreMark is load/store heavy, and the recent MEM-stage\n+  byte-lane improvement indicates this benchmark is sensitive to the memory\n+  datapath. Prior structural frontend decoupling and prediction attempts paid\n+  too much fetch-path timing cost, so a backend bypass is a more focused IPC\n+  improvement.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a direct MEM-stage load-result bypass into the EX operand forwarding\n+  network. When a load sits in EX/MEM and a younger instruction in ID/EX reads\n+  the same rd, EX should use the current MEM load_data instead of stalling for\n+  the value to reach MEM/WB. The bypass must be disabled for misaligned/trapping\n+  loads so dependent instructions retain the old architectural register value,\n+  and dmem backpressure should still freeze the pipeline until valid load data\n+  is available. This removes the normal one-cycle load-use penalty without\n+  adding branch prediction, fetch queues, or nret changes.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose the combinational aligned load_data value and a bypass-valid signal gated off for misaligned or trapping loads.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a MEM-load forwarding input and select it for rs1/rs2 operands ahead of the older MEM/WB path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Teach forwarding to distinguish EX/MEM ALU-result forwarding from EX/MEM load-data bypass forwarding.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the unconditional load-use bubble when the new MEM-to-EX bypass can safely satisfy the dependency, while preserving stalls under dmem backpressure.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the MEM-stage bypass value and valid signal into the forwarding and EX-stage operand paths.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-