{"type":"text","timestamp":1778647810076,"sessionID":"ses_1e055373cffewiHYtNqTg3x5s5","part":{"id":"prt_e1fabbe470016sDri3OAD3N23n","messageID":"msg_e1fab448c0018Uvz4xNK8PQrCt","sessionID":"ses_1e055373cffewiHYtNqTg3x5s5","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a structural hypothesis that retimes PC-relative address generation into the ID/EX register. It avoids the failed fetch-path redirect/prediction work while targeting the EX branch/jump/AUIPC timing path with no intended CPI change.","time":{"start":1778647809607,"end":1778647810075},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0752d3c47c65c2c9016a04030158c081998697a2d12522e276","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778647816974,"sessionID":"ses_1e055373cffewiHYtNqTg3x5s5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_AmvhGgmuY2wyCzOQMXN67E19","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r8s1\n+title: \"Precompute PC-relative targets in ID\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core already benefits from a registered lookahead hot-branch predictor, but EX still recomputes pc+4 and pc+imm for branches, JAL, AUIPC, link writeback, redirect targets, prediction correction, and RVFI pc_wdata. Prior IF-side prediction and buffering attempts regressed because they put extra compares, target adds, or queue control on the fetch PC path. A narrower structural retime can instead move PC-relative adders behind the existing ID/EX register and shorten the EX resolve/writeback muxing without changing speculation policy.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add registered pc_plus4 and pc_plus_imm fields to the ID/EX payload, computed in id_stage from the fetched PC and decoded immediate. In ex_stage, use those registered values for branch targets, JAL targets, JAL/JALR link data, normal sequential pc_next, and AUIPC writeback, while keeping JALR's rs1+imm calculation in EX because it depends on forwarded rs1. This should reduce the always-active EX pc-add and branch/jump result mux depth while preserving the single-issue nret=1 RVFI contract, existing hot-branch predictor behavior, and all memory/divide stall rules.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Extend id_ex_t with registered pc_plus4 and pc_plus_imm fields carried from decode into execute.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute pc+4 and pc+imm when latching ID/EX so EX receives registered PC-relative addresses.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Consume the registered PC-relative values for branch/JAL targets, sequential pc_next, JAL link writeback, and AUIPC results while leaving JALR target formation in EX.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r8s1\n+title: \"Precompute PC-relative targets in ID\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core already benefits from a registered lookahead hot-branch predictor, but EX still recomputes pc+4 and pc+imm for branches, JAL, AUIPC, link writeback, redirect targets, prediction correction, and RVFI pc_wdata. Prior IF-side prediction and buffering attempts regressed because they put extra compares, target adds, or queue control on the fetch PC path. A narrower structural retime can instead move PC-relative adders behind the existing ID/EX register and shorten the EX resolve/writeback muxing without changing speculation policy.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add registered pc_plus4 and pc_plus_imm fields to the ID/EX payload, computed in id_stage from the fetched PC and decoded immediate. In ex_stage, use those registered values for branch targets, JAL targets, JAL/JALR link data, normal sequential pc_next, and AUIPC writeback, while keeping JALR's rs1+imm calculation in EX because it depends on forwarded rs1. This should reduce the always-active EX pc-add and branch/jump result mux depth while preserving the single-issue nret=1 RVFI contract, existing hot-branch predictor behavior, and all memory/divide stall rules.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Extend id_ex_t with registered pc_plus4 and pc_plus_imm fields carried from decode into execute.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute pc+4 and pc+imm when latching ID/EX so EX receives registered PC-relative addresses.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Consume the registered PC-relative values for branch/JAL targets, sequential pc_next, JAL link writeback, and AUIPC results while leaving JALR target formation in EX.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r8s1\n+title: \"Precompute PC-relative targets in ID\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core already benefits from a registered lookahead hot-branch predictor, but EX still recomputes pc+4 and pc+imm for branches, JAL, AUIPC, link writeback, redirect targets, prediction correction, and RVFI pc_wdata. Prior IF-side prediction and buffering attempts regressed because they put extra compares, target adds, or queue control on the fetch PC path. A narrower structural retime can instead move PC-relative adders behind the existing ID/EX register and shorten the EX resolve/writeback muxing without changing speculation policy.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add registered pc_plus4 and pc_plus_imm fields to the ID/EX payload, computed in id_stage from the fetched PC and decoded immediate. In ex_stage, use those registered values for branch targets, JAL targets, JAL/JALR link data, normal sequential pc_next, and AUIPC writeback, while keeping JALR's rs1+imm calculation in EX because it depends on forwarded rs1. This should reduce the always-active EX pc-add and branch/jump result mux depth while preserving the single-issue nret=1 RVFI contract, existing hot-branch predictor behavior, and all memory/divide stall rules.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Extend id_ex_t with registered pc_plus4 and pc_plus_imm fields carried from decode into execute.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute pc+4 and pc+imm when latching ID/EX so EX receives registered PC-relative addresses.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Consume the registered PC-relative values for branch/JAL targets, sequential pc_next, JAL link writeback, and AUIPC results while leaving JALR target formation in EX.\"\n","additions":17,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778647816970,"end":1778647816973}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0752d3c47c65c2c9016a040301fda081999bc3689e99d3117f"}},"id":"prt_e1fabc01c001XMLYmp8g1n9cYP","sessionID":"ses_1e055373cffewiHYtNqTg3x5s5","messageID":"msg_e1fab448c0018Uvz4xNK8PQrCt"}}
