{"type":"text","timestamp":1778648762892,"sessionID":"ses_1e047495bffeJfUrSCjYHqe3vM","part":{"id":"prt_e1fba4864002EUTVRLMpOEENAg","messageID":"msg_e1fb989b6002gHTj8gqvClj860","sessionID":"ses_1e047495bffeJfUrSCjYHqe3vM","type":"text","text":"I’m going to write a structural hypothesis that removes the remaining multiplier family from the always-active ALU path via a dedicated multi-cycle M-unit. This is intentionally narrower than broad pipeline retiming and directly addresses why the earlier high-half-only side unit failed: low-half MUL kept the multiplier on the common path.","time":{"start":1778648762468,"end":1778648762892},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0f511b86e29bbe3d016a0406ba5f808198bc9b748c5b47c083","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778648773311,"sessionID":"ses_1e047495bffeJfUrSCjYHqe3vM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_EYatyCmSUnC9irl2zCZDWnfw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r9s1\n+title: Move all MUL ops to a side unit\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful DIV/REM side unit showed that this core benefits when rare or\n+  heavy RV32M arithmetic is removed from the always-active EX ALU result path.\n+  A later high-half-multiply side unit regressed because low-half MUL still left\n+  a 32x32 multiplier in the common ALU mux, so the structural timing bottleneck\n+  was not actually removed while new stall control was added.\n+\n+  The remaining untried structural split is to move the entire MUL family,\n+  including ALU_MUL, out of alu.sv. CoreMark will pay extra cycles on multiply\n+  instructions, but the normal integer, branch, load/store, and predictor paths\n+  should lose the parallel signed/unsigned multiplier fanout and wide M-result\n+  muxing that currently sit in the EX stage.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a dedicated multi-cycle multiply side unit for MUL, MULH, MULHU, and\n+  MULHSU, using the same start/wait/consume pattern as the existing DIV/REM\n+  unit. In normal builds, alu.sv should no longer implement real multiply\n+  datapaths; EX detects multiply opcodes, starts the side unit, emits bubbles\n+  while the result is pending, and writes the side-unit result into EX/MEM when\n+  complete. Under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the existing algebraic ALTOPS\n+  substitutions so the fast formal contract remains unchanged.\n+\n+  This should improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax by removing all multiplier variants\n+  from the common ALU result path, not just the high-half cases. The risk is\n+  CoreMark CPI loss if MUL is frequent, so the unit should be low-latency and\n+  preferably registered around 16x16 partial products rather than a long\n+  shift-add loop.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a low-latency multi-cycle RV32M multiply unit covering MUL, MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU with start, busy, done, clear, and result signals.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real multiply datapaths from the normal combinational ALU path while preserving RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions for all M-extension opcodes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect multiply operations, stall EX while the multiply unit runs, preserve forwarded operand values for RVFI, and select the side-unit result into EX/MEM on completion.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Reuse the existing EX-busy pipeline hold path for multiply stalls alongside DIV/REM stalls without changing dmem, imem, redirect, or load-use priorities.\"\n+  - file: test/test_mul_unit.py\n+    description: \"Add exact RV32M multiply-vector coverage for the new side unit so moving MUL out of alu.sv does not weaken the arithmetic correctness invariant.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,43 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r9s1\n+title: Move all MUL ops to a side unit\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful DIV/REM side unit showed that this core benefits when rare or\n+  heavy RV32M arithmetic is removed from the always-active EX ALU result path.\n+  A later high-half-multiply side unit regressed because low-half MUL still left\n+  a 32x32 multiplier in the common ALU mux, so the structural timing bottleneck\n+  was not actually removed while new stall control was added.\n+\n+  The remaining untried structural split is to move the entire MUL family,\n+  including ALU_MUL, out of alu.sv. CoreMark will pay extra cycles on multiply\n+  instructions, but the normal integer, branch, load/store, and predictor paths\n+  should lose the parallel signed/unsigned multiplier fanout and wide M-result\n+  muxing that currently sit in the EX stage.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a dedicated multi-cycle multiply side unit for MUL, MULH, MULHU, and\n+  MULHSU, using the same start/wait/consume pattern as the existing DIV/REM\n+  unit. In normal builds, alu.sv should no longer implement real multiply\n+  datapaths; EX detects multiply opcodes, starts the side unit, emits bubbles\n+  while the result is pending, and writes the side-unit result into EX/MEM when\n+  complete. Under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the existing algebraic ALTOPS\n+  substitutions so the fast formal contract remains unchanged.\n+\n+  This should improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax by removing all multiplier variants\n+  from the common ALU result path, not just the high-half cases. The risk is\n+  CoreMark CPI loss if MUL is frequent, so the unit should be low-latency and\n+  preferably registered around 16x16 partial products rather than a long\n+  shift-add loop.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a low-latency multi-cycle RV32M multiply unit covering MUL, MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU with start, busy, done, clear, and result signals.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real multiply datapaths from the normal combinational ALU path while preserving RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions for all M-extension opcodes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect multiply operations, stall EX while the multiply unit runs, preserve forwarded operand values for RVFI, and select the side-unit result into EX/MEM on completion.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Reuse the existing EX-busy pipeline hold path for multiply stalls alongside DIV/REM stalls without changing dmem, imem, redirect, or load-use priorities.\"\n+  - file: test/test_mul_unit.py\n+    description: \"Add exact RV32M multiply-vector coverage for the new side unit so moving MUL out of alu.sv does not weaken the arithmetic correctness invariant.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,43 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r9s1\n+title: Move all MUL ops to a side unit\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful DIV/REM side unit showed that this core benefits when rare or\n+  heavy RV32M arithmetic is removed from the always-active EX ALU result path.\n+  A later high-half-multiply side unit regressed because low-half MUL still left\n+  a 32x32 multiplier in the common ALU mux, so the structural timing bottleneck\n+  was not actually removed while new stall control was added.\n+\n+  The remaining untried structural split is to move the entire MUL family,\n+  including ALU_MUL, out of alu.sv. CoreMark will pay extra cycles on multiply\n+  instructions, but the normal integer, branch, load/store, and predictor paths\n+  should lose the parallel signed/unsigned multiplier fanout and wide M-result\n+  muxing that currently sit in the EX stage.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a dedicated multi-cycle multiply side unit for MUL, MULH, MULHU, and\n+  MULHSU, using the same start/wait/consume pattern as the existing DIV/REM\n+  unit. In normal builds, alu.sv should no longer implement real multiply\n+  datapaths; EX detects multiply opcodes, starts the side unit, emits bubbles\n+  while the result is pending, and writes the side-unit result into EX/MEM when\n+  complete. Under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the existing algebraic ALTOPS\n+  substitutions so the fast formal contract remains unchanged.\n+\n+  This should improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax by removing all multiplier variants\n+  from the common ALU result path, not just the high-half cases. The risk is\n+  CoreMark CPI loss if MUL is frequent, so the unit should be low-latency and\n+  preferably registered around 16x16 partial products rather than a long\n+  shift-add loop.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a low-latency multi-cycle RV32M multiply unit covering MUL, MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU with start, busy, done, clear, and result signals.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real multiply datapaths from the normal combinational ALU path while preserving RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions for all M-extension opcodes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect multiply operations, stall EX while the multiply unit runs, preserve forwarded operand values for RVFI, and select the side-unit result into EX/MEM on completion.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Reuse the existing EX-busy pipeline hold path for multiply stalls alongside DIV/REM stalls without changing dmem, imem, redirect, or load-use priorities.\"\n+  - file: test/test_mul_unit.py\n+    description: \"Add exact RV32M multiply-vector coverage for the new side unit so moving MUL out of alu.sv does not weaken the arithmetic correctness invariant.\"\n","additions":43,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778648773308,"end":1778648773311}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f511b86e29bbe3d016a0406baceec8198b57cdcdde0faaf03"}},"id":"prt_e1fba4a0c002ZVXH7mDo6HCGH2","sessionID":"ses_1e047495bffeJfUrSCjYHqe3vM","messageID":"msg_e1fb989b6002gHTj8gqvClj860"}}
