{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778648781087,"sessionID":"ses_1e047495bffeJfUrSCjYHqe3vM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_FUVlhzW8uhSEEyYQxrLUySWe","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260513-002-r9s1\n2: title: Move all MUL ops to a side unit\n3: category: structural\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The successful DIV/REM side unit showed that this core benefits when rare or\n6:   heavy RV32M arithmetic is removed from the always-active EX ALU result path.\n7:   A later high-half-multiply side unit regressed because low-half MUL still left\n8:   a 32x32 multiplier in the common ALU mux, so the structural timing bottleneck\n9:   was not actually removed while new stall control was added.\n10: \n11:   The remaining untried structural split is to move the entire MUL family,\n12:   including ALU_MUL, out of alu.sv. CoreMark will pay extra cycles on multiply\n13:   instructions, but the normal integer, branch, load/store, and predictor paths\n14:   should lose the parallel signed/unsigned multiplier fanout and wide M-result\n15:   muxing that currently sit in the EX stage.\n16: hypothesis: |\n17:   Add a dedicated multi-cycle multiply side unit for MUL, MULH, MULHU, and\n18:   MULHSU, using the same start/wait/consume pattern as the existing DIV/REM\n19:   unit. In normal builds, alu.sv should no longer implement real multiply\n20:   datapaths; EX detects multiply opcodes, starts the side unit, emits bubbles\n21:   while the result is pending, and writes the side-unit result into EX/MEM when\n22:   complete. Under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the existing algebraic ALTOPS\n23:   substitutions so the fast formal contract remains unchanged.\n24: \n25:   This should improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax by removing all multiplier variants\n26:   from the common ALU result path, not just the high-half cases. The risk is\n27:   CoreMark CPI loss if MUL is frequent, so the unit should be low-latency and\n28:   preferably registered around 16x16 partial products rather than a long\n29:   shift-add loop.\n30: expected_impact:\n31:   fitness_delta_pct: 4\n32:   confidence: low\n33: changes:\n34:   - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n35:     description: \"Add a low-latency multi-cycle RV32M multiply unit covering MUL, MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU with start, busy, done, clear, and result signals.\"\n36:   - file: rtl/alu.sv\n37:     description: \"Remove real multiply datapaths from the normal combinational ALU path while preserving RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions for all M-extension opcodes.\"\n38:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n39:     description: \"Detect multiply operations, stall EX while the multiply unit runs, preserve forwarded operand values for RVFI, and select the side-unit result into EX/MEM on completion.\"\n40:   - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n41:     description: \"Reuse the existing EX-busy pipeline hold path for multiply stalls alongside DIV/REM stalls without changing dmem, imem, redirect, or load-use priorities.\"\n42:   - file: test/test_mul_unit.py\n43:     description: \"Add exact RV32M multiply-vector coverage for the new side unit so moving MUL out of alu.sv does not weaken the arithmetic correctness invariant.\"\n\n(End of file - total 43 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-002-r9s1\ntitle: Move all MUL ops to a side unit\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The successful DIV/REM side unit showed that this core benefits when rare or\n  heavy RV32M arithmetic is removed from the always-active EX ALU result path.\n  A later high-half-multiply side unit regressed because low-half MUL still left\n  a 32x32 multiplier in the common ALU mux, so the structural timing bottleneck\n  was not actually removed while new stall control was added.\n\n  The remaining untried structural split is to move the entire MUL family,\n  including ALU_MUL, out of alu.sv. CoreMark will pay extra cycles on multiply\n  instructions, but the normal integer, branch, load/store, and predictor paths\n  should lose the parallel signed/unsigned multiplier fanout and wide M-result\n  muxing that currently sit in the EX stage.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a dedicated multi-cycle multiply side unit for MUL, MULH, MULHU, and\n  MULHSU, using the same start/wait/consume pattern as the existing DIV/REM\n  unit. In normal builds, alu.sv should no longer implement real multiply\n  datapaths; EX detects multiply opcodes, starts the side unit, emits bubbles","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778648781067,"end":1778648781086}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e6da76f35add417016a0406cbfb70819a87722e2d52de8233"}},"id":"prt_e1fba8d3b001NkRfOcRtiXO26H","sessionID":"ses_1e047495bffeJfUrSCjYHqe3vM","messageID":"msg_e1fba730d001qQTOfO7fPRDqWU"}}
