{"type":"text","timestamp":1778651577074,"sessionID":"ses_1e01b78dfffecGWHjhodBZE5QZ","part":{"id":"prt_e1fe535d600107HYigfTQzwDzK","messageID":"msg_e1fe4b4ca001XDw6kIKX1ftAWS","sessionID":"ses_1e01b78dfffecGWHjhodBZE5QZ","type":"text","text":"The history points to one safe predictor lane: keep the successful one-entry registered lookahead predictor intact, avoid new IF compares or delayed promotion, and instead reduce the EX correction/update cost around prediction metadata. I’m writing a hypothesis focused on gating prediction validation with an explicit “predicted taken” bit so non-control instructions avoid the always-active predicted-PC correction path.","time":{"start":1778651575766,"end":1778651577074},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d41517e3c33477a016a0411b781248198b0b7ea1c522f9e2e","phase":"commentary"}}}}
