{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778651600006,"sessionID":"ses_1e01b78dfffecGWHjhodBZE5QZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_e78yAq0FoGzwBpeIE7fYSS8H","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r11s2\n+title: \"Gate predictor correction compare\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The one-entry registered lookahead predictor is the only predictor variant\n+  that has improved this core, because it keeps tag comparison and target\n+  generation off the current IF next-PC path. Later predictor changes regressed\n+  when they added IF lookup entries, delayed useful updates, or polluted the\n+  successful update policy. The remaining predictor opportunity is therefore to\n+  keep the IF predictor behavior unchanged while trimming the EX-stage\n+  prediction validation logic that now sits on every valid instruction.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Carry an explicit predicted-taken bit alongside predicted_pc_next through\n+  IF/ID and ID/EX. The IF stage sets it only when consuming the already-armed\n+  lookahead target; otherwise it remains false for normal sequential fetches.\n+  EX can then form redirect only for actual control-flow instructions or for an\n+  instruction that was fetched under a prediction, instead of feeding every\n+  non-control instruction through the wide resolved_pc_next-versus-predicted_pc\n+  correction compare. Keep the existing one-entry lookahead table, single\n+  seq_pc prearm compare, backward-branch plus direct-JAL training policy, and\n+  RVFI pc_wdata behavior unchanged. This should preserve the proven CPI win\n+  while reducing EX redirect fanout and Fmax pressure without adding any new IF\n+  critical-path logic.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a predicted_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t so prediction validation can distinguish sequential fetches from consumed lookahead predictions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drive predicted_taken from armed_valid_q when emitting the fetched instruction, while leaving the one-entry lookahead predictor and update policy unchanged.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch predicted_taken through the ID/EX register alongside predicted_pc_next without changing decode, raw rs fields, or RVFI-visible source data.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Gate the redirect correction compare with actual branch/jump control or predicted_taken, preserving correction for stale predictions, loop exits, jumps, and misalignment traps.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r11s2\n+title: \"Gate predictor correction compare\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The one-entry registered lookahead predictor is the only predictor variant\n+  that has improved this core, because it keeps tag comparison and target\n+  generation off the current IF next-PC path. Later predictor changes regressed\n+  when they added IF lookup entries, delayed useful updates, or polluted the\n+  successful update policy. The remaining predictor opportunity is therefore to\n+  keep the IF predictor behavior unchanged while trimming the EX-stage\n+  prediction validation logic that now sits on every valid instruction.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Carry an explicit predicted-taken bit alongside predicted_pc_next through\n+  IF/ID and ID/EX. The IF stage sets it only when consuming the already-armed\n+  lookahead target; otherwise it remains false for normal sequential fetches.\n+  EX can then form redirect only for actual control-flow instructions or for an\n+  instruction that was fetched under a prediction, instead of feeding every\n+  non-control instruction through the wide resolved_pc_next-versus-predicted_pc\n+  correction compare. Keep the existing one-entry lookahead table, single\n+  seq_pc prearm compare, backward-branch plus direct-JAL training policy, and\n+  RVFI pc_wdata behavior unchanged. This should preserve the proven CPI win\n+  while reducing EX redirect fanout and Fmax pressure without adding any new IF\n+  critical-path logic.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a predicted_taken bit to if_id_t and id_ex_t so prediction validation can distinguish sequential fetches from consumed lookahead predictions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drive predicted_taken from armed_valid_q when emitting the fetched instruction, while leaving the one-entry lookahead predictor and update policy unchanged.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch predicted_taken through the ID/EX register alongside predicted_pc_next without changing decode, raw rs fields, or RVFI-visible source data.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Gate the redirect correction compare with actual branch/jump control or predicted_taken, preserving correction for stale predictions, loop exits, jumps, and misalignment traps.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-