{"type":"text","timestamp":1778652375764,"sessionID":"ses_1e00f92cfffe3TG6UPRBYYBNdl","part":{"id":"prt_e1ff16985001hu1Z0Sg4iG7Uw1","messageID":"msg_e1ff0b0e5001A0OoF6QcHad146","sessionID":"ses_1e00f92cfffe3TG6UPRBYYBNdl","type":"text","text":"I’m adding a single-file hypothesis that keeps the proven one-entry lookahead predictor and proposes redirect-target prearming, avoiding new predictor entries or fetch-path target computation.","time":{"start":1778652375429,"end":1778652375763},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0873b9386ba66b04016a0414d722048199b9be14128a58933f","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778652381916,"sessionID":"ses_1e00f92cfffe3TG6UPRBYYBNdl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_2CFgOrSW92BrLpVeDfu4yih4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r12s2\n+title: \"Redirect-target predictor prearm\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only predictor variant that improved fitness is the current one-entry\n+  registered lookahead predictor: it compares the stored hot PC against pc+4\n+  one cycle early, then the fetch next-PC mux consumes only registered armed\n+  state. Later predictor attempts regressed when they added IF lookup entries,\n+  delayed promotion, changed the update policy, or added carried validation\n+  bits. A remaining gap is that lookahead arming only happens along sequential\n+  fetch. When an EX redirect lands directly on a previously learned hot control\n+  instruction, the predictor cannot be armed because the predecessor PC was not\n+  fetched sequentially.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Preserve the existing single-entry predictor table, update policy, and\n+  registered armed-target next-PC mux, but add redirect-target prearming inside\n+  if_stage. On a redirect, compare the redirect target against the registered\n+  predictor PC and, if it matches, set armed_valid_q and armed_target_q for the\n+  next cycle while loading the redirected PC. This keeps target computation and\n+  current-PC tag lookup out of the fetch next-PC path, but lets a branch or JAL\n+  reached by another redirect consume the same prearmed prediction immediately\n+  on its first fetched cycle. Correctness remains unchanged because EX still\n+  carries predicted_pc_next and redirects on any mismatch.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"When handling an EX redirect, prearm the existing one-entry lookahead predictor if the redirected PC matches the stored predictor PC, without adding another IF lookup entry or changing predictor training.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r12s2\n+title: \"Redirect-target predictor prearm\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only predictor variant that improved fitness is the current one-entry\n+  registered lookahead predictor: it compares the stored hot PC against pc+4\n+  one cycle early, then the fetch next-PC mux consumes only registered armed\n+  state. Later predictor attempts regressed when they added IF lookup entries,\n+  delayed promotion, changed the update policy, or added carried validation\n+  bits. A remaining gap is that lookahead arming only happens along sequential\n+  fetch. When an EX redirect lands directly on a previously learned hot control\n+  instruction, the predictor cannot be armed because the predecessor PC was not\n+  fetched sequentially.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Preserve the existing single-entry predictor table, update policy, and\n+  registered armed-target next-PC mux, but add redirect-target prearming inside\n+  if_stage. On a redirect, compare the redirect target against the registered\n+  predictor PC and, if it matches, set armed_valid_q and armed_target_q for the\n+  next cycle while loading the redirected PC. This keeps target computation and\n+  current-PC tag lookup out of the fetch next-PC path, but lets a branch or JAL\n+  reached by another redirect consume the same prearmed prediction immediately\n+  on its first fetched cycle. Correctness remains unchanged because EX still\n+  carries predicted_pc_next and redirects on any mismatch.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"When handling an EX redirect, prearm the existing one-entry lookahead predictor if the redirected PC matches the stored predictor PC, without adding another IF lookup entry or changing predictor training.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r12s2\n+title: \"Redirect-target predictor prearm\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only predictor variant that improved fitness is the current one-entry\n+  registered lookahead predictor: it compares the stored hot PC against pc+4\n+  one cycle early, then the fetch next-PC mux consumes only registered armed\n+  state. Later predictor attempts regressed when they added IF lookup entries,\n+  delayed promotion, changed the update policy, or added carried validation\n+  bits. A remaining gap is that lookahead arming only happens along sequential\n+  fetch. When an EX redirect lands directly on a previously learned hot control\n+  instruction, the predictor cannot be armed because the predecessor PC was not\n+  fetched sequentially.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Preserve the existing single-entry predictor table, update policy, and\n+  registered armed-target next-PC mux, but add redirect-target prearming inside\n+  if_stage. On a redirect, compare the redirect target against the registered\n+  predictor PC and, if it matches, set armed_valid_q and armed_target_q for the\n+  next cycle while loading the redirected PC. This keeps target computation and\n+  current-PC tag lookup out of the fetch next-PC path, but lets a branch or JAL\n+  reached by another redirect consume the same prearmed prediction immediately\n+  on its first fetched cycle. Correctness remains unchanged because EX still\n+  carries predicted_pc_next and redirects on any mismatch.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"When handling an EX redirect, prearm the existing one-entry lookahead predictor if the redirected PC matches the stored predictor PC, without adding another IF lookup entry or changing predictor training.\"\n","additions":29,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778652381911,"end":1778652381915}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0873b9386ba66b04016a0414d7ae108199bf8ccb8fe0f34fe3"}},"id":"prt_e1ff16ad70010zRGwSsklJ0A0X","sessionID":"ses_1e00f92cfffe3TG6UPRBYYBNdl","messageID":"msg_e1ff0b0e5001A0OoF6QcHad146"}}
