{"type":"text","timestamp":1778653686327,"sessionID":"ses_1dffbc9fdffelgPiozcTfM7y6H","part":{"id":"prt_e20056686001Fsii7K4ZyYlBk1","messageID":"msg_e20045f8f001SvmRDLDQ1hV1Yf","sessionID":"ses_1dffbc9fdffelgPiozcTfM7y6H","type":"text","text":"The strongest predictor lesson is to preserve the successful one-entry registered lookahead shape and avoid adding current-PC lookup, extra entries, delayed promotion, or redirect-path prearming. I’m writing a narrow predictor hypothesis that keeps behavior equivalent but keys the lookahead entry by the predecessor PC so the IF arming compare no longer loads the `pc+4` adder result.","time":{"start":1778653685382,"end":1778653686326},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d7a82167cd0cb53016a0419f51eb0819aad397e8532dfe3da","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778653692245,"sessionID":"ses_1dffbc9fdffelgPiozcTfM7y6H","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_DUSIS8rFFvoB69IMVg0BNRnZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r13s2\n+title: \"Predecessor-keyed lookahead predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only predictor variant that improved this core is the current one-entry\n+  registered lookahead predictor. Follow-up attempts regressed when they added\n+  IF lookup entries, redirect-path prearming, candidate promotion, carried\n+  validation bits, or update-policy changes. The remaining useful predictor\n+  angle is therefore to keep the proven CPI behavior while shaving the arming\n+  logic from the front-end timing cone.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Change the one-entry lookahead predictor to store the sequential predecessor\n+  PC of the learned hot control-flow instruction instead of the control-flow\n+  instruction PC itself. IF can then prearm with a direct `pred_prev_pc == pc`\n+  comparison while fetching the predecessor, rather than comparing the stored\n+  branch PC against `pc + 4`. The fetched next PC and predicted target behavior\n+  stay equivalent for sequential arrivals, but the `pc+4` adder output no longer\n+  feeds the predictor tag compare fanout. This preserves the successful single\n+  registered armed-target next-PC mux and current backward-branch plus direct-JAL\n+  training policy while targeting a small Fmax improvement with no intended CPI\n+  loss.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Store pred_update_pc - 4 as the predictor key and prearm from a direct predecessor-PC comparison against the current fetch PC, keeping the existing single armed target mux and update policy.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated t