rediction is consumed, and gate replacement by different direct-JAL updates while keeping the IF lookup and next-PC mux one-entry/registered.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose whether each predictor update came from a taken backward conditional branch or a direct JAL so if_stage can apply loop-entry replacement priority without changing redirect, RVFI pc_next, or trap behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the predictor update class signal from EX to IF alongside the existing update valid, PC, and target signals.\"\n","additions":33,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778654530523,"end":1778654530526}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_00e5fb42643675f1016a041d3eef608198835f98255df7b7b0"}},"id":"prt_e20123e31001Pq33ih4O21zknP","sessionID":"ses_1dfee91c7ffeyWt73JHJ32TtO9","messageID":"msg_e201193d3001bwJ1QqWwfWM2R1"}}
