{"type":"text","timestamp":1778655831294,"sessionID":"ses_1dfdae7b8ffeVh91A2mMudZVFe","part":{"id":"prt_e20261f9a001M8G6yEEI4g3AcH","messageID":"msg_e2025431b001AhmftOp6nxlBpG","sessionID":"ses_1dfdae7b8ffeVh91A2mMudZVFe","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor history shows the only successful path is the existing one-entry registered lookahead predictor; follow-ups regressed when they added IF lookup entries, delayed promotion, or changed JAL/backward-branch training. I’m writing a narrower next hypothesis that keeps that fetch datapath but adds loop-exit awareness for fixed-trip loops.","time":{"start":1778655829914,"end":1778655831293},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_00d99891874db31b016a042255ca74819ab807d6bfc2084836","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778655839988,"sessionID":"ses_1dfdae7b8ffeVh91A2mMudZVFe","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_bdcEXngMwHg8gsy7WM5Agr8Y","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r15s2\n+title: Loop-exit aware lookahead predictor\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current one-entry registered lookahead predictor is the only predictor\n+  variant that has improved this core because the fetch next-PC mux consumes\n+  only registered armed state. It still predicts every learned backward loop\n+  branch as taken, so fixed-trip CoreMark loops pay one full EX-corrected\n+  mispredict at each loop exit. Avoiding those exit flushes targets remaining\n+  branch CPI while preserving the successful no-current-PC-lookup timing shape.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny loop-exit counter overlay to the existing one-entry lookahead\n+  predictor. Keep the same active PC/target entry, the same single sequential\n+  lookahead prearm point, and the same registered armed-target next-PC mux, but\n+  also learn the observed taken-count for the active backward branch when that\n+  branch eventually falls through. On later visits, suppress arming for exactly\n+  the learned exit iteration so the fetch stream naturally continues to pc+4;\n+  EX still validates predicted_pc_next and repairs any stale or irregular loop\n+  behavior. This should recover CoreMark loop-exit bubbles without adding a\n+  second IF lookup entry, redirect prearming, candidate promotion, or direct-JAL\n+  filtering, all of which have regressed previously.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Extend the existing one-entry lookahead predictor with small loop iteration/trip-count registers, suppressing armed_valid_q on the learned loop-exit iteration while leaving the next-PC mux driven only by registered armed state.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Provide predictor update information for both taken backward branches and the not-taken fall-through of the active loop branch so IF can learn and refresh the loop trip count without changing RVFI pc_next or redirect correction semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the added loop-outcome predictor update signals between EX and IF while preserving the nret=1 top-level IO contract and existing stall/flush priorities.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,31 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r15s2\n+title: Loop-exit aware lookahead predictor\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current one-entry registered lookahead predictor is the only predictor\n+  variant that has improved this core because the fetch next-PC mux consumes\n+  only registered armed state. It still predicts every learned backward loop\n+  branch as taken, so fixed-trip CoreMark loops pay one full EX-corrected\n+  mispredict at each loop exit. Avoiding those exit flushes targets remaining\n+  branch CPI while preserving the successful no-current-PC-lookup timing shape.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny loop-exit counter overlay to the existing one-entry lookahead\n+  predictor. Keep the same active PC/target entry, the same single sequential\n