{"type":"text","timestamp":1778641992547,"sessionID":"ses_1e0adc51effeSv1hzl81ETFJPA","part":{"id":"prt_e1f52fac2001CsxoTPYdK2KZzp","messageID":"msg_e1f52b99f001jV6J8aBsZhtHaZ","sessionID":"ses_1e0adc51effeSv1hzl81ETFJPA","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a single predictor hypothesis that preserves the current IF critical path by doing only sequential fetch in IF and issuing static taken predictions one stage later from ID.","time":{"start":1778641992386,"end":1778641992546},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_089113f6c4c5ee08016a03ec48483c819aa53647c3ce74c43a","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778641999350,"sessionID":"ses_1e0adc51effeSv1hzl81ETFJPA","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_7Pl7YbP1UEHCnrRhdVA7Fsh0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\n+title: \"ID-stage static control predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core resolves every taken branch and jump in EX, so CoreMark loop\n+  backs and direct jumps pay a two-instruction wrong-path flush. Prior IF-stage\n+  static and BTB predictors showed that eliminating this penalty can help CPI,\n+  but putting immediate decode, target add, tag compare, or predictor RAM lookup\n+  on the fetch next-PC path costs too much Fmax on Tang Nano 20K.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move the lightweight static predictor out of IF and into ID. IF should remain\n+  a simple sequential pc+4 fetch unless an existing redirect arrives, while ID\n+  decodes the fetched instruction and redirects one stage early for aligned JAL\n+  and aligned backward conditional branches. Carry the ID-predicted next PC into\n+  EX so the branch/jump resolver redirects only when the actual next PC differs\n+  from the prediction. This keeps predictor work off the front-end critical path\n+  and still saves one of the two taken-control-flow bubbles in CoreMark loops.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add an ID/EX predicted-next-PC field so EX can compare the static ID prediction with the actual resolved next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire ID-stage prediction redirect signals to IF and route the carried predicted next PC into EX resolution.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept an ID-stage prediction redirect with lower priority than EX correction, update the PC to the predicted target, and squash the sequential wrong-path fetch.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute a static aligned JAL/backward-branch prediction from the already-fetched instruction, emit an early redirect, and latch the predicted next PC into ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare actual branch/jump next PC against the carried prediction and issue a correction redirect only on mismatch, preserving misalignment trap behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,31 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\n+title: \"ID-stage static control predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core resolves every taken branch and jump in EX, so CoreMark loop\n+  backs and direct jumps pay a two-instruction wrong-path flush. Prior IF-stage\n+  static and BTB predictors showed that eliminating this penalty can help CPI,\n+  but putting immediate decode, target add, tag compare, or predictor RAM lookup\n+  on the fetch next-PC path costs too much Fmax on Tang Nano 20K.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move the lightweight static predictor out of IF and into ID. IF should remain\n+  a simple sequential pc+4 fetch unless an existing redirect arrives, while ID\n+  decodes the fetched instruction and redirects one stage early for aligned JAL\n+  and aligned backward conditional branches. Carry the ID-predicted next PC into\n+  EX so the branch/jump resolver redirects only when the actual next PC differs\n+  from the prediction. This keeps predictor work off the front-end critical path\n+  and still saves one of the two taken-control-flow bubbles in CoreMark loops.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add an ID/EX predicted-next-PC field so EX can compare the static ID prediction with the actual resolved next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire ID-stage prediction redirect signals to IF and route the carried predicted next PC into EX resolution.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept an ID-stage prediction redirect with lower priority than EX correction, update the PC to the predicted target, and squash the sequential wrong-path fetch.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute a static aligned JAL/backward-branch prediction from the already-fetched instruction, emit an early redirect, and latch the predicted next PC into ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare actual branch/jump next PC against the carried prediction and issue a correction redirect only on mismatch, preserving misalignment trap behavior.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/ex