{"type":"text","timestamp":1778645887890,"sessionID":"ses_1e0725864ffe4XbN4xjJvqC7Oq","part":{"id":"prt_e1f8e684f001K5cyIo4NKgh12Y","messageID":"msg_e1f8dcc0f0012d4MQonOW5fNiu","sessionID":"ses_1e0725864ffe4XbN4xjJvqC7Oq","type":"text","text":"The predictor history shows same-cycle IF/ID prediction logic repeatedly regressed, so I’m writing a narrower hypothesis: a one-cycle lookahead hot-branch predictor that pre-arms the next sequential PC from registered state instead of comparing/adding on the current fetch PC critical path.","time":{"start":1778645887055,"end":1778645887889},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_07582b468744777b016a03fb7ebdc48199929d739f0914cc37","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778645896487,"sessionID":"ses_1e0725864ffe4XbN4xjJvqC7Oq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_IoHuue2JbTZ4KPeBFLYfFK2g","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Lookahead hot-branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts lost because the prediction decision sat directly on the current IF next-PC path: immediate decode, target adders, tag compares, or same-cycle ID redirects reduced Fmax more than CoreMark gained from fewer taken-branch bubbles. CoreMark still has hot loop-back branches, so the remaining promising predictor angle is to keep prediction state registered and move the lookup one cycle ahead of the branch fetch.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry hot control-flow predictor that is updated from EX with the resolved PC and target of taken backward branches and direct jumps, but consume it through a one-cycle sequential lookahead. While fetching PC N, compare the registered predictor PC against N+4 and latch a prearmed prediction for the next sequential fetch; when PC N+4 is fetched on the following cycle, the IF next-PC mux uses only the registered prearmed target, not a same-cycle tag compare or target adder. Carry the predicted next PC with the instruction so EX redirects only on a real mismatch. This should recover loop-back taken-branch bubbles while avoiding the timing pattern that broke the prior IF BTB, static, loop, and return predictors.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles so EX can validate a prearmed prediction without changing RVFI retirement fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-entry EX-updated hot control-flow predictor and a registered sequential lookahead hit/target path; the current fetch PC path uses only prearmed registered metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch the IF-stage predicted next PC through ID/EX alongside the existing instruction metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare the carried predicted next PC with the resolved branch/jump next PC, suppress redirects on correct predictions, correct mispredictions, and emit predictor update information.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire prediction metadata and EX predictor-update signals between IF, ID, and EX while preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Lookahead hot-branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts lost because the prediction decision sat directly on the current IF next-PC path: immediate decode, target adders, tag compares, or same-cycle ID redirects reduced Fmax more than CoreMark gained from fewer taken-branch bubbles. CoreMark still has hot loop-back branches, so the remaining promising predictor angle is to keep prediction state registered and move the lookup one cycle ahead of the branch fetch.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry hot control-flow predictor that is updated from EX with the resolve