{"type":"text","timestamp":1778646582968,"sessionID":"ses_1e0674db0ffeEmw3uLEWkzZ3An","part":{"id":"prt_e1f9905850018Rqx4TrcQ8zzKx","messageID":"msg_e1f98d6250014tDL2L1GW14vGd","sessionID":"ses_1e0674db0ffeEmw3uLEWkzZ3An","type":"text","text":"The prior data points rule out any predictor that puts current-PC tag lookup, immediate decode, or target add directly into the IF next-PC mux. The best remaining predictor-only proposal is to extend the already-successful registered lookahead predictor from one learned target to two entries so nested CoreMark loops or direct jumps do not evict each other, while keeping prediction consumption prearmed and off the current fetch mux.","time":{"start":1778646582661,"end":1778646582966},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_04c83eac90ae91b9016a03fe36907c8198b96e124a066a3974","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778646589950,"sessionID":"ses_1e0674db0ffeEmw3uLEWkzZ3An","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_2Md1RCrctIsw6gaqHTuAC1aE","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r7s2\n+title: \"Two-entry lookahead hot predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current one-entry lookahead predictor is the first predictor variant that improved fitness because it keeps the current IF next-PC mux free of tag comparisons and target adders. CoreMark still contains nested loops and direct control-flow edges, so a single learned PC can be evicted by another hot edge and lose most of the warm predictor benefit between repeated visits.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Expand the existing registered lookahead predictor in if_stage from one entry to two small entries, updated from the same EX-resolved taken backward branches and direct jumps. While fetching PC N, compare N+4 against both registered entry PCs only to prearm the following cycle; when the predicted instruction is actually fetched, the next-PC mux still consumes only the already-registered armed target. This should reduce predictor thrashing on nested CoreMark loops and call/jump structure without reintroducing the timing pattern that broke current-PC BTBs, static IF decode, ID redirects, or return predictors.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the single pred_valid/pred_pc/pred_target entry with two registered entries, add simple replacement on EX updates, and prearm from a two-entry lookahead match while keeping the current next-PC mux driven only by armed_valid_q and armed_target_q.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bone