{"type":"text","timestamp":1778647780796,"sessionID":"ses_1e055368cffemZ0UAPWBAj72oY","part":{"id":"prt_e1fab4cc4001QmW0VJsa12xbQT","messageID":"msg_e1fab115b001XgJxeuJT5uOzhN","sessionID":"ses_1e055368cffemZ0UAPWBAj72oY","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a single-file predictor hypothesis that preserves the successful one-entry lookahead datapath and only changes predictor training policy in EX, avoiding the failed two-entry and same-cycle lookup patterns.","time":{"start":1778647780548,"end":1778647780795},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0931fe815f6521e1016a0402e4724c819ab81173472995f097","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778647783741,"sessionID":"ses_1e055368cffemZ0UAPWBAj72oY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_4jrznWyabXUqbLzeXdeFQcNC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r8s2\n+title: \"Loop-only lookahead training\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best predictor is the one-entry sequential lookahead design because\n+  it keeps tag comparison off the current IF next-PC mux. The failed two-entry\n+  expansion suggests the next predictor gain should not add more IF arming\n+  compares or replacement state. A simpler way to reduce one-entry thrash is to\n+  stop training it with direct JAL targets that may be cold calls or one-shot\n+  control transfers and can evict the hot CoreMark loop-back branch.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restrict the existing lookahead predictor update to taken backward conditional\n+  branches only, leaving the IF-side predictor entry, lookahead compare, armed\n+  target mux, and carried predicted_pc_next metadata unchanged. This preserves\n+  the timing shape that improved fitness while making the single predictor entry\n+  less prone to pollution from direct jumps. The tradeoff is giving up some JAL\n+  predictions, but CoreMark's most valuable repeated control-flow edges should\n+  be loop branches, so the hotter entry should improve iterations per cycle with\n+  little or no Fmax cost.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Narrow pred_update_valid so the one-entry lookahead predictor trains only on valid, legal, taken backward conditional branches instead of also replacing the entry with direct JAL targets.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /User