{"type":"text","timestamp":1778648682011,"sessionID":"ses_1e04749c1ffe3HmEGmw03933P3","part":{"id":"prt_e1fb90b3b001KawnbKzC8c7Ebg","messageID":"msg_e1fb8d9a00018LfG7Sh8hXdkER","sessionID":"ses_1e04749c1ffe3HmEGmw03933P3","type":"text","text":"The predictor history points to preserving the successful one-entry registered lookahead timing shape. The strongest new angle is not adding IF entries or filtering all JALs, but adding an EX-update-side candidate/promotion policy so one-shot control edges do not evict the active hot entry unless they repeat.","time":{"start":1778648681275,"end":1778648682010},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0f61ac828420daf4016a0406692d788199b54bdbc192e3b073","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778648687730,"sessionID":"ses_1e04749c1ffe3HmEGmw03933P3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_sOcezrfEx1MI0br6bcAp4kya","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r9s2\n+title: \"Promote repeated lookahead targets\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The one-entry registered lookahead predictor is the only predictor variant that improved fitness because IF consumes only prearmed registered state. Later attempts regressed when they added a second IF compare/replacement path or filtered out direct JAL updates entirely, which suggests the entry needs better update selectivity without changing the fetch critical path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the existing active one-entry lookahead predictor and its single seq_pc compare, but add a non-fetch-path candidate entry used only by the EX update logic. A newly resolved taken backward branch or direct JAL first records as the candidate; it replaces the active predictor only when the same PC is seen again, while updates to the current active PC still refresh its target immediately. This should reduce eviction by one-shot calls and cold control-flow edges while still allowing repeated JALs and nested-loop branches to become predicted, avoiding both the failed two-entry IF lookup and the failed all-JAL filtering policies.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a candidate PC/target register pair to the existing lookahead predictor update path; promote candidates to the active entry only after a repeated resolved update while keeping the IF lookup as one active-entry seq_pc compare and one armed target mux.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"I